5v5 Escort Battle

Victory Conditions:
1. Attackers: Escort the payload to the destination within the specified time.
2. Defenders: Prevent the payload from reaching the destination within the specified time.

Special Mechanics:
1. Approach or stick on the payload to advance it forward.
2. You can adjust the String Energy Network while in a Safe Zone or waiting to respawn.
3. You can resupply your tactical items multiple times.
4. Team members will respawn together periodically.

<NoticePC_TextBlod>Participation Rules: </>Unlock Ranked matches at Lv. 10.

<NoticePC_TextBlod>Season Duration: </>Each season lasts for approximately two months. At the end of each season, you will earn rewards based on the highest rank achieved in the season. At the beginning of each season, you need to play placement matches again to determine your starting rank.

<NoticePC_TextBlod>Ranks: </>There are a total of nine ranks, each with different divisions and Strinovium Point limits (see image above).

<NoticePC_TextBlod>Promotion and Demotion: </>When you reach the maximum number of stars in each division, one more victory will promote you, granting you one star (some exceptional Navigators may skip one additional division upon promotion). After losing all your stars in a division, one more loss will trigger a demotion of divisions or ranks.

<NoticePC_TextBlod>Rank Protection: </>No star loss on defeats in Substance or Molecule ranks; no demotion in Proton rank after losing all stars in a division.

ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.5_Content: Next up, we have multiple missing person reports: Male, 22 years old, approximately 1.8 meters tall, wearing black-framed glasses, has a circular birthmark on his left arm, dressed in a black tactical jacket, went missing near the Ironwest Station on the night of March 30. A reward is offered for information on the missing person's whereabouts. Contact information: XXXXX
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.6_Content: Call to reduce large-scale events during this unprecedented period: In the interest of public safety, the Golden String concert originally scheduled for this Sunday at Orpheus Music Hall in Arton City has been canceled. Tickets will be refunded via the original payment methods. We sincerely apologize for the inconvenience.
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.4_Content: Area Restriction Notice: Effective immediately, dangerous areas within Preton will be sealed off. Citizens are advised to avoid restricted routes.
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.8_Content: Alien Purger recruitment: P.U.S authorities are establishing additional purge squads for exploration, combat, and protection missions. Volunteers from the public are welcome to apply. Registration and interviewing will be handled by the Urbino Emergency Response Center.
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.7_Content: The string sequence disruption incident has escalated and is now classified as an S-level security crisis, aka Outbreak. Citizens are urged to cooperate with official efforts. In the face of this crisis, collaboration and mutual aid are the only solutions.
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.12_Content: The lockdown in Preton has been lifted. The Strinova Capture-the-Flag Championship, scheduled for next month, will proceed as planned. Astral Sanctuary, a subsidiary of Urbino, will provide special support, offering free check-ups for participants.
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.9_Content: Crystallized powder recovery: As dust concentration declines, traces of crystallized powder have been found in some suburban areas. If you discover mutated crystal fragments, as shown in the image, please contact the BAA immediately. A response team will be dispatched to collect samples.
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.11_Content: The Outbreak crisis is nearing its conclusion. This Sunday, P.U.S will hold a press conference in Elmond to disclose information and conduct a full review of the incident. Citizens are welcome to register online to watch the live broadcast.
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.3_Content: Regarding the distribution of supplies, citizens are asked to report their household information to the BAA using communication devices. P.U.S officials will deliver protective supplies to designated areas by 6 p.m. daily.
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.2_Content: The public is asked to provide clues and intelligence regarding the string sequence disruption. If you have any information, please contact the P.U.S Bureau of Anomalous Affairs.
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.10_Content: According to the Strinova Meteorological Bureau, the dust concentration in Preton has shown a downward trend over the past week, with peak levels dropping from 36% to 2% and an average concentration of 3.94%. The air quality index is excellent.
ActivityBiochemicalModeTV.1_Content: Multiple incidents involving abnormally infected individuals have been reported in Preton. P.U.S authorities are investigating the cause of the incidents in order to find a solution.

ActivityCNYFireStory.6_StoryContext: While you watch the fireworks with Maddelena, she feels bittersweet at the fleeting scenery. You comfort her that the purpose of art is to capture beauty in eternity.
ActivityCNYFireStory.4_StoryContext: You join Lawine on the observation deck to watch the fireworks celebrations. The grand display brought out some homesickness in Lawine, making her feel small and lonely. But it's okay—you're there to be a safe haven for the wanderer.
ActivityCNYFireStory.2_StoryContext: The brave Michele and her partner, the Navigator, embark on an adventure together—a bonus quest with endless rewards!
ActivityCNYFireStory.3_StoryContext: Busy with her work, Audrey has been unable to help out with the preparations. To make sure she feels included and to reward her for all her hard work, you decide to join her in the fireworks celebrations.
ActivityCNYFireStory.5_StoryContext: After your busy week helping with the celebration preparations, Kokona invites you to watch the fireworks together. The mighty Captain Sea Bunny uses her makeshift telescope to “see into the future” - for both you and Strinova, the future is sure to get better and better!
ActivityCNYFireStory.1_StoryContext: As the festival approaches, the work at Astral Sanctuary finally comes to an end. Together, you head to the fireworks celebration. Standing side by side, you share the breathtaking view, no words needed to understand the unspoken thoughts between you.

The future is bright,
so seize the moment.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.12_Content:
The journey of a thousand miles
begins with a single step.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.4_Content:
In countless homes, each passing stay,
old ways yield on the new day.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.7_Content:
As the calendar adds new years,
spring casts the land anew.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.5_Content:
Basking in the spring breeze,
riding the wind to the heavens.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.9_Content:
Hold one in your heart,
till death do you part.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.8_Content:
Fireworks bid old dreams farewell,
the world is in good cheer.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.11_Content:
The next step
is to go further.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.6_Content:
May you see the century,
time proves not to be your enemy.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.13_Content:
If you know the enemy and know yourself,
you need not fear the result of a hundred battles.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.10_Content:
May your wealth grow
and prosperity overflow.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.3_Content:
As joy fills home, New Year's cheer.
Wealth and fortune, springtime nears.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.1_Content:
Though I have no wings like those of the bright phoenix for my body,
I feel the harmonious heartbeat of the sacred.
ActivityCNYLuckyLotteryPool.2_Content:
The wind blows, breaking against waves.

ActivityCommonStory.6_StoryContext:
xx Year x Month x Day, Sunday, Clear


Today, while delivering food to Astral Sanctuary, I stumbled upon a new job opportunity:

"Recruiting diving guides for the Summer Isles. Free meals, diving gear, and opportunities for close encounters with marine life."

Summer Isles, underwater ruins, and mysterious treasures...
This rare job (adventure) opportunity is too good to miss~
Just as Celestia asked me to help the Navigator break their bad habit of staying indoors and working overtime, I decided to bring the Navigator along.

To claim the legendary treasure, we must conquer various trials.
For instance, the underwater combat race—how did I pass that level again?
Oh, right, I remember causing a huge underwater inferno, after which the other contestants vanished...
(Note: This was not against the rules!)

But everyone seemed to think it was some kind of magical, new underwater show. Instead of causing panic, the storm brought cheers and applause! This is a real opportunity. The organizers want me to perform the "Deep Sea Inferno" for more audiences, and my hourly wage will jump from 50 to 100 Dream Tokens!

With this, I can save up more quickly to buy Kanami's album!
Current savings progress: 800/3000 Dream Tokens.
Keep going, Eika, you got this~!

Oh, and I've entrusted the treasure map fragments obtained from the trials to the reliable Navigator.
ActivityCommonStory.2_StoryContext:
The young bartender told me her name—Fuchsia, a flower from old Earth. She wasn't secretive about her personal information, yet she spoke with little interest, like a passerby in a hurry, unwilling to leave a trace in others' memories.

"Are you the bartender here?"

She nodded.

"Besides bartending, do you handle other things? Like opening and closing the bar... In other words, were you the first to arrive here today?"

Her eyes turned cautious: "That's private. I can't tell you."

I handed her my detective card with a sincere demeanor. Under my gaze, she relented, turning away awkwardly: "<SalonOutline>Anyway, Meredith—the lady with the hood—wasn't the first to arrive. I opened the door for her.</>”

Then she looked at me again, probing: "<SalonOutline>You get what I mean?</>”

I winked at her, putting a finger to my lips in a "shh" gesture.
ActivityCommonStory.1_Desc:
My eyes wandered around the bar before being quickly drawn to a woman sitting on a single sofa, playing poker.Everything about her screamed “mysterious”, from the smile on her lips and her hidden gaze to her figure flickering under the light. Could this be my client?
 
(Approach her and introduce yourself.)
ActivityCommonStory.50_StoryContext:
"You don't belong here, painter. This is a battlefield."
"Weapons aren't meant for this world either, but I paint them nonetheless. We need this power now."
Among another separated squad, Maddelena stands her ground against the alien creatures. She neither retreats nor follows the order to fall back.
Artists recreate human forms to contain scattered memories. However, the souls drifting through the wilderness lack guidance and become distorted upon contact with the crystals.
Looking at the twisted creations, Maddelena sighs and tightens her grip on her weapon. An artist's creative impulse can awaken at any moment, even now.
"Draw inspiration from the chaos, Navigator."
ActivityCommonStory.47_StoryContext:
"The sky is filled with dust, marking the intensity of the infection here."
Standing on the streets of Preton, Celestia briefly casts her gaze to the sky before turning her attention to the distant Komos Tower. It stands tall and majestic, its sleek design fully intact, much like its counterparts elsewhere.
But that is precisely where the problem lies...
Though the tower is supposed to ensure regional stability, reverstring phenomena are happening right here. The dust grows thicker, nearly masking the sky, sinking Preton into deeper shadows.
"Navigator, this isn't like anything we've faced before..."
"I’m uneasy... I can barely see the stars anymore..."
For once, the resilient healer reveals a glimpse of vulnerability, as if something in this place stirs her deepest instincts. To uncover the truth, there’s no choice but to venture further into this region.
ActivityCommonStory.49_StoryContext:
"I hurt my teammate, fired two shots at his head..."
The exploration team is attacked by alien creatures. Some are separated; some are turned into monsters, and those who remain have no choice but to fire at their former comrades—simply to protect themselves.
When the first monster appears, it is met with a relentless barrage.
But as they witness their allies transform into alien creatures, their aim falters, and the trigger feels heavier in their hands...
"Keep firing. Fulfill your duty."
A calm and resolute voice steadies them all. Yvette, the P.U.S researcher, no longer her usual shy self, displays decisiveness and resolve to find solutions.
"Fay says defeating them is the only way to save them."
"Their souls will return to their backup bodies, and the Navigator will collect their scattered memories. Our duty is to protect the Navigator."
ActivityCommonStory.48_StoryContext:
"Authorized personnel only."
The P.U.S task force has established a blockade on the outskirts of Preton, bordering the wilderness. The team comprises unfamiliar faces, yet the emblems on their sleeves mark them as elite soldiers deployed from various regions. Among them is Kokona, who, setting aside her usual laid-back and carefree demeanor, now shares in the seriousness and tension that grips the rest.
"P.U.S agreed to a joint investigation. You have no authority to stop us."
"Much remains unknown about this area. We at P.U.S cannot risk the safety of our partners..."
 Celestia presents an access permit bearing the P.U.S emblem, which puts Kokona in a difficult position. Her usual relaxed demeanor only returns when she notices me standing on the side.
"I have faith the Navigator can lead us down the right path."
"My team will accompany you to ensure you and the Navigator stay safe."
ActivityCommonStory.2_StoryIntro: The stoic bartender focused on mixing drinks
ActivityCommonStory.48_StoryIntro: They claim nothing is out of the ordinary, yet their expressions are filled with unease.
ActivityCommonStory.47_StoryIntro: Born from the unusual amidst the ordinary.
ActivityCommonStory.52_StoryIntro: They are merely a subset of humanity, unable to grasp the human trait of forgetting.
ActivityCommonStory.49_StoryIntro: The foolish crumble in the face of danger, while the wise seek solutions.
ActivityCommonStory.52_StoryContext:
Countless people gather toward us, calling one another's names and recounting important memories.
Before we know it, our numbers outmatch theirs, and the once-intimidating monsters no longer instill fear in us.
The fear has instead been replaced by...
A great sorrow.
The final gunshot abruptly cuts off this brief sorrow, marking the end of the last Omega Core.
Cheers ring out from the majority, while some sink into prolonged silence.
"The world has not yet recovered from The Collapse. The truth behind the mutation remains unexplained. What challenges will we face in the future?"
In my experience, it's rare to see Bai Mo wear such a pensive expression.
"This world, or perhaps this very body, is burdened with shackles. Where does the true freedom lead, my friend?"

The dust-covered sky finally clears.
Celestia has found a way to heal the infected by harnessing the human trait of forgetting—something we had always evaded.
Destruction, the cycle of life and death, and this very crisis—human greed has catalyzed disaster time and again...
 
Yet it is through our intrinsic greed that humanity has survived. It's our exploration of nature, our pursuit of truth, and our thirst for the unknown that will guide us toward a brave new world.
"Remember, Navigator. Remember for all of us, as the only one in the world who will never forget."
ActivityCommonStory.51_StoryIntro: Who created you? We must find the answer.
ActivityCommonStory.51_StoryContext:
We find ourselves ensnared in a fierce battle against the Omega Cores. The souls dwelling within the crystals casts powerful obsessions onto everyone present, clouding and disrupting their minds and reason, attempting to turn us into abominations just like them.
But in the midst of adversity, the most steadfast and pure individuals often live to save the day.
"Recklessly hurting others just out of obsession and instinct. Such extreme emotions... Not even The Scissors are this despicable!"
Now, Michele, a rookie investigator who seemingly has no place here, stands firm before the Omega Core, heroically shielding everyone.
"The P.U.S creed teaches us unity and selflessness."
"I will not lose to these slaves of instinct, Navigator!"
ActivityCommonStory.50_StoryIntro: As of now, a warrior and an artist share the same duty.
ActivityCommonStory.46_StoryIntro: Rather than a letter, this feels more like an assignment.
ActivityCommonStory.46_StoryContext:
To the Navigator:

We urgently need your assistance.
The string sequence shift in Preton has reawakened the souls in the True Wilderness.
They have possessed innocent people, robbing them of their sanity and twisting their forms.
Please defeat those creatures, gather intelligence, and recover the lost souls.
To facilitate your mission, P.U.S has coordinated with Urbino to secure the area. Attached is your access permit.
ActivityCommonStory.31_StoryName: An Uninvited Guest at the Snowy Manor

ActivityConcertLevel.1_LevelRoleContent: “Took you long enough to get here, my savior! Good thing at least you're reliable. I'll be waiting for you in the practice room. Come over soon!”
ActivityConcertLevel.2_LevelRoleContent: “What to do... such an important task left to me... I can't handle it...!”
ActivityConcertLevel.4_LevelRoleContent: “Performing is an idol's specialty! Hehe... Don't worry, Navigator, I won't let you down!”
ActivityConcertLevel.3_LevelRoleContent: “Piano? Don't worry. Just be natural and enjoy the music!”
ActivityConcertLevel.5_LevelRoleContent: “Music brings peace to the mind. I have no objection to your invitation, Navigator. I'll be there.”

ActivityConcertStory.5_Content:
“Navigator! Wait, no... It's 'conductor' now... you're here! Let's get started!”
Kanami's face is full of enthusiasm. Gazing at the practice room mirror, she's long imagined seeing this side of herself, displaying a musical prowess that none could match.
But when she finally saw who she wanted to see, it was in the lounge at night, body covered in a conductor's coat.
“Huh? Did I mess something up? Kanami just wanted to give the Navigator a surprise... After all, Lawine and the other said as much, and even gave me such beautiful clothes...”
Kanami lowers her head, a flurry of emotions on her red face.
Surprise, self-blame, bashfulness...
“A-Are you surprised? I...”
Her face becomes redder, and she fumbles over herself even more.
“I-I'll definitely become your favorite idol!”
The girl speaks while covering her face with a sheet of music. The conductor in front of her gives a simple nod and starts turning to leave.
Feelings were conveyed, albeit with a misunderstanding.
But even so... this still counts as being bold and achieving one's goal... doesn't it?
ActivityConcertStory.6_Content:
“It's you. No need to worry. I'm not the most experienced in classical music, but I'm familiar with music theory.”
When the sunset comes, the lone shadow in the practice room finally comes to a stop.
“Not good enough again... No, I guess it can count as a success. What do you think, Navigator?”
The lone figure keeps their distance, holding their saxophone.
“...I wouldn't feel very comfortable being so close, but if you feel it will help you conduct, I won't voice any complaints.”
Lawine speaks calmly, maintaining a mysterious profile in the sunset.
A calming and nostalgic étude is played once more.
One can't help but be confident that the performance will be one that lingers in the memory.
ActivityConcertStory.3_Content:
“Bai Mo suddenly dumped this task on me. I'm really a little... uh... unconfident.”
In the practice room, Maddelena looks at me with a violin in her hand. Through her glasses, I can see a lost look on her pale and youthful face.
“I really... uhm... what if my sister sees? Eh...? Just let you guide me? Treat it as a paintbrush...?”
Instead of replying, I simply raise my baton and start conducting with the score. Maddelena makes a lot of harsh and pained sounds, and it takes till dark for us to get the atmosphere right.
“Can you feel it, Navigator? In this way, even someone ordinary like me can keep up with someone like Bai Mo...!”
She's got it the wrong way around. The ordinary timbre is the most important part of any performance. Without the violin's thread, the entire performance may as well be empty talk.
Maddelena's shy smile gives off the airs of a reserved calmness that is hers alone. With it, one can't help but be intoxicated by the sound of the music...
ActivityConcertStory.4_Content:
Outside the practice room, I hear the sound of piano movements slowly flowing out from a crack in the door.
Even after I open the door, the girl remains focused. Her light, slender fingers dance along the black and white keys, continuing until they strike the last note on a black.
“Music is fascinating. It's so different from medicine and anything else I've dabbled in. It's so easy to get drawn in without even noticing.”
As she speaks, she lifts the little hat on her head and shoots me a playful wink.
“Want to try piano four hands? You won't be able to conduct properly without giving it a go.”
Before I can react, Kokona pulls me to her side.
“Don't worry, just follow my lead.”
Our melody steadily blooms into a cheerful dance of keys.
Kokona might be right. If you spend all your time on the podium, you lose sight of the full picture.
“I'm looking forward to the performance. If we could continue playing together in the future... I think I'd like that.”
There's a hint of caring expectation in her smile...
ActivityConcertStory.7_Content:
Standing on the podium and looking into the packed crowd, you feel surprisingly at ease.
You know that each and every member of your band has great faith in you.
The next step is to just raise your baton and kick off a grand performance. With the music of the new year, the band will bid the past farewell and welcome blessings anew.
This serves as both an invitation and a hope for joyful news.
We wish you happiness, all of you who love Strinova.
ActivityConcertStory.2_Content:
When I arrived at the practice room, I found Bai Mo already perched in a chair, hard at work on his études, glancing at me through the corner of his eye.
“What do you think, friend? A good pitch, is it not?”
I must admit that Bai Mo is quite the accomplished musician. Knowing his unreliable nature, it's hard to imagine he could be as elegant and gentle as he is now.
“Come and conduct. Let's have a proper practice performance.”
I raise my baton and extend an invitation for him to begin.
“Alright! Check this out!”
The tuba becomes spirited, moving in lockstep with the conductor's baton and leading the rhythm - most fitting for Bai Mo, indeed.
“Capital, my friend! But now is not the time to trade compliments. There is still much work to be done.”
The corners of his mouth are raised in expectation. It seems that he has all the faith in the world that I'll make this a success.
ActivityConcertStory.7_Title: Finale: Thank You for a Successful Performance
ActivityConcertStory.1_Content:
At the start of the new year, a special invitation from Urbino was handed to you.
This message comes from Bai Mo, head of the Urbino Business Alliance. Having been inspired to celebrate the New Year with music, Bai Mo has called for talented musicians from far and wide to participate in the event.
Yet Bai Mo has greatly underestimated the opinions of these talented individuals, and their rift I fear is so great as to have destroyed any promise of this great performance. It is for this reason I especially wanted to pass this letter to you...
“There's no time, my friend. Only you can help me now! Only you can put these weirdos... Ahem, I mean, only you can get everyone on the same page to make this performance a success. I'm counting on you!”
                                               - Bai Mo

ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.1_DesThird: Navigator, the only thing I can reveal is that you're safe now. No one will disturb our little game... Heh, curious for more, are you?
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.1_DesFirst: Surprised, are you? Even butterflies like to spread their wings at the café occasionally.

ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.1_EndDesTwo: Shame. You were so close... Take a break. Have a cup of coffee. I can offer you a hint if you'd like.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.2_DesSecond: Record, think, deduct. To me, these are as natural and vital as breathing.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.3_EndDesTwo: Not bad. Next time, let's clean the remaining dirt together.

ActivityStrangeThiefStory.23_ContentAside:
- Multiple clue cards mention surveillance footage. Who installed the cameras?
     - “Me, the mastermind, of course. I knew exactly where everyone was.”

- Did you really forget about the time? How did you manage to show up at the exact moment Lawine entered Kidd Hall?
     - “Why do you think I had cameras installed, Navigator? As a competent member of the Phantom Thieves, I adjusted my time of arrival based on the situation to ensure the item would be unveiled on time.”

- Why did you plan a bomb? I don't get it.
     - “Because I wanted something fun! Besides, I had to blow up the surveillance devices and the secret passage. I wasn't going to tell everyone that Kanami and the gang stole the final auction item.”

- Had I failed to solve the puzzle in time, would you still have detonated the bomb?
     - “While I had other methods to take out the cameras without the risk of injuries, Navigator, I knew what you were capable of. A simple puzzle was a piece of cake for you.”

- Does that mean you gave Ming the details of the auction item?
     - “Not bad. Did you notice my call? Besides that, I was also the person responsible for the secret passage. I'd wanted them to have the item for a while. It was more fun than purchasing it and giving it to them.”

- What about the codes on the clue cards? According to your plan, Lawine and the others wouldn't have known about you.
     - “You figured that out as well, Navigator? Well, I thought it would be cool, that's all. You know me. I'm an indispensable member of the Phantom Thieves. The family has to stay together.”

- Was the self-portrait of Mr. Black Cat a part of your plan as well?
     - “How dare you... No, certainly not. I could never have expected it! They've ruined my reputation...”

- What exactly was the final auction item?
     - “I can't tell you. Why don't you ask The Scissors? Hahahaha!”

Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Not just sugar... Adding some milk protein and tea polyphenols would make things even better.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId131: If possible... a liquid nutrient that's easy to absorb would be best.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row14_PlayerOption1: Sounds like... You want some milk tea?
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Navigator, do you know any good sources of sugar?
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row11_PlayerOption1: If it's urgent, a glucose shot could help.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row17_PlayerOption2: I just happen to have a ticket to Dreamscape Park.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row4_PlayerOption2: Have you been working too hard? Maybe you should take a break.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I'm ok for now. But it's risky.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Fay... I'm feeling really unmotivated right now. I can't think of anything.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Fay says we need some more high-energy carbohydrates.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row17_PlayerOption1: Speaking of which, have you heard anything about the “Journey of Dreams” event at the amusement park?
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row4_PlayerOption1: That sounds serious. Are you okay?
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId131: If this goes on, I won't be able to do any research at all.

Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row18_PlayerOption1: That's what you expect from the No. 1 investigator.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Otherwise, I'd totally come to hang out with you!
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId101: The park is really buzzing today.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row14_PlayerOption1: How'd you end up helping out at the candy house?
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Guess where I am right now?
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Heheh... Knew you'd never get it!
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row20_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Hmm... aside from reports of a mysterious bear-like creature with a sweet tooth, nothing major.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row22_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Helping out at the candy house and seeing everyone's smiles made it all worth it!
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId101: They've transformed the rides into a candy wonderland.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row3_PlayerOption1: Knowing you, I'd bet you're at home gaming.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row9_PlayerOption1: I actually snagged a ticket from someone...
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId101: I'm helping out at the candy house in the amusement park!
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId101: That's why I offered to come in and help as an undercover investigator.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row18_PlayerOption2: So, did you spot any safety concerns?
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId101: There's a cupcake Ferris wheel and a donut bumper car... it's like I'm living inside a dream!
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row23_TextContent_FromRoleId101: After all... even The Scissors wouldn't want to spoil this sweet dream, right?
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId101: The candy house is packed with customers... I'm swamped...
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row21_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Even though my investigator skills weren't much in play this time...
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row16_TextContent_FromRoleId101: The event's drawing in tons of visitors, and park security just can't handle it.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId101: You've got to come by Michele's Candy House!
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row26_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Anyway, I've gotta get back to helping out. See ya!

Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId137: My heart was all a-flutter at the thought of a surprise encounter with the Navigator!
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId137: And before I knew it, it was already closing time.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row24_TextContent_FromRoleId137: I wonder... did that kid with my ticket have sweet dreams?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId137: But, there were so many amazing sights and delicious treats that I kinda forgot about finding you...
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row20_TextContent_FromRoleId137: I spotted the ticket with my signature in the crowd today.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Can I count on you to join me there?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId137: The tour must be wrapping up, right?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row21_TextContent_FromRoleId137: I just wanted to see how you'd react, Navigator.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row19_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Hehe! Gotcha! I know you already gave away the ticket.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Hehe! It's all thanks to destiny's magic!
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Make sure you wrap up your magical day without any regrets! ☆
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId137: So, how was the “Journey of Dreams” event at the amusement park? Did it blow your mind?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row16_TextContent_FromRoleId137: I'm right outside the candy house, looking over the Ferris wheel.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId137: So... do you think you could spend those last few moments with Kanami?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row22_PlayerOption1: I'm sorry if it wasn't what you hoped.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row23_TextContent_FromRoleId137: No worries! As an idol, I’m here to spread dreams! ☆
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Did you hit up all the popular photo spots?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Have you tried all their special desserts?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Winning that special prize at a Kanami fan meetup... it’s proof of the Navigator's devotion to me!
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row25_TextContent_FromRoleId137: And... next time, you better not dodge Kanami!
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Kanami also snuck her way into the amusement park!

ApartmentBirthdaySeasonComments.3_Desc: Are you an autumn baby too? Let's take a trip to the countryside together and soak in the beauty of the fall scenery.
ApartmentBirthdaySeasonComments.1_Desc: So... your birthday's in spring? It's a perfect season for an outing together in such warm weather.
ApartmentBirthdaySeasonComments.2_Desc: On summer nights, the stars twinkle endlessly. Maybe we could watch them together sometime.
ApartmentBirthdaySeasonComments.4_Desc: When it's time to celebrate your birthday, we can also have a snowball fight together~

ApartmentMapCfg.1001_Desc: Strinova Guide at your service. Please do not try gliding after drinking sparkling water.
ApartmentMapCfg.124_Desc: Kokona briefly served in the P.U.S training unit, but she prefers frontline work.
ApartmentMapCfg.128_Desc: Lawine had her personnel file redacted when she left P.U.S. No one even knows her true name...
ApartmentMapCfg.137_Desc: Visit the idol singer Kanami in her home. It must feel magical.
ApartmentMapCfg.146_Desc: Celestia's Astral Sanctuary is a major investment project of Urbino.
ApartmentMapCfg.112_Desc: The mysterious mercenary girl gave her address to you and only you. This shows how much you mean to her.
ApartmentMapCfg.105_Desc: Grove Bank is an important asset of the Grove Family and Audrey's pride.
ApartmentMapCfg.101_Desc: As the governing body of Strinova, P.U.S enforces strict discipline, with all members residing in assigned dormitories.
ApartmentMapCfg.131_Desc: Whenever asked about her address, Yvette quickly provides the location of the P.U.S dormitory before nervously clutching the hem of her clothes...
ApartmentMapCfg.107_Desc: Maddelena believes that designers are always either creating or seeking inspiration!

ApartmentMapLoadingTips.15_Tips: “This is the song of my soul, the gift I would like to offer the world♪” - Kanami
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.54_Tips: Yvette has a mysterious past... Perhaps she is waiting for someone she can open up to.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.52_Tips: Yvette prefers cold beverages and desserts, but she has never fallen ill because of them.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.57_Tips: Yvette offers to make Fay all kinds of clothes, but Fay refuses every time. Yet, Yvette does not intend to give up.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.16_Tips: Yvette is familiar with all sorts of creatures and helps them survive in this world.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.22_Tips: As the head of Astral Sanctuary, she is respected by all healthcare workers, yet she remains humble and kind.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.14_Tips: Nobunaga wakes up each day in pain, haunted by his kin's betrayal.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.20_Tips: A healer cannot heal herself; Celestia needs a doctor too when she treats others.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.19_Tips: She has spent countless nights observing and waiting. Will the stars ever respond to her?
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.42_Tips: If you're unsure what takeout to order, ask Kokona—she'll have a special recommendation.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.12_Tips: In the dead of night, Reiichi always seems to be kind and gentle.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.55_Tips: At work, Yvette is always calm and rational, seemingly unaffected by anything...
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.34_Tips: As a capitalist, Audrey isn't fully mature yet, still holding onto the weakness of kindness.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.30_Tips: Audrey often talks about her family.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.32_Tips: Audrey's firepower and sharp mind are her greatest weapons.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.5_Tips: Audrey once suffered from Collapse Syndrome, but she still managed to piece herself back together with the help of her diary and the kindness of others.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.29_Tips: Audrey's crown is a family heirloom and symbol. Its shiny, tough exterior encases a soft, pure core, embodying the essence of family.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.31_Tips: Though she can analyze situations rationally and stay calm through any change, her blushing reveals everything when she's complimented.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.21_Tips: The stars she lights up become the path for those who follow.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.49_Tips: If you're seeking artistic surprises in life, contact designer Maddelena Leary.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.10_Tips: Chase your dream if you still have one, for all dreams can be realized right here!
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.65_Tips: Fuchsia is capable of completely hiding her presence when necessary.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.46_Tips: To Maddelena, her art consultant is also her best model.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.44_Tips: Kokona's strong drive and proactiveness come from her innate curiosity, always open to trying unusual dishes.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.45_Tips: Kokona excels at taking care of others emotionally, but she rarely allows herself to be cared for.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.41_Tips: Kokona's room is always cluttered with random items, so watch your step when visiting.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.7_Tips: Kokona claims the secret to staying energized is smiling a lot.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.37_Tips: It's obvious that Lawine and the impulsive Ming are complementary to one another. On the battlefield, they inspire their teammates' fighting spirit.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.39_Tips: Clenching the Pulse Blade, showing its sharp edge in the dark of the night, Lawine tells herself to bid farewell to the past.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.6_Tips: Lawine is an outstanding budo practitioner, thanks to her childhood experiences.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.38_Tips: Formerly one of the top investigators of P.U.S, Lawine had a bright future.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.36_Tips: Lawine enjoys drinking tea, especially green tea.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.35_Tips: Lawine is meticulous and diligent, two contributing factors to her becoming an enforcer of The Scissors.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.40_Tips: Lawine hones her body and mind through budō, dispelling her doubts.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.50_Tips: Legend has it that the tiny Maddelena can be seen gathering materials for her art all around the world.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.48_Tips: When people hear the name Ms. Leary, they usually think of Maddelena's older sister, a renowned artist.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.24_Tips: On countless nights, Michele lies awake contemplating the true meaning of justice.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.9_Tips: The fire in Ming's eyes has never been extinguished. As a child, she protected the weak with her fists. Nowadays, she points her gun at oppressors.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.1_Tips: Celestia still gets upset when dealing with disobedient patients.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.3_Tips: Celestia likes drinking coffee in hopes that its rich aroma will dispel her internal conflict.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.17_Tips: Celestia tweaks her coffee mix daily, to the point where she's lost count of all the variations.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.59_Tips: Kanami's dream started from her desire to shine.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.63_Tips: A song is a record of life. Kanami sings for the silent unseen.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.27_Tips: Michele's father left her Mighty Meow—a steadfast companion and a strong pillar of support.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.25_Tips: Michele's father is her greatest role model and the person she aspires to become.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.66_Tips: The solitary Fuchsia has no concept of or attachment to family.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.47_Tips: Maddelena believes that designers are always either creating or seeking inspiration!
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.8_Tips: Maddelena's world is simple—create beautiful art and let everyone enjoy this new realm.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.51_Tips: The majority of Maddelena's designs arise from accidents and troubles.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.13_Tips: Bai Mo has a spray can gifted to him by his best friend. He uses it to leave behind his mark of memories and liberty in the True Wilderness.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.28_Tips: Michele isn't fond of going solo. She always hopes for a partner to join her on her adventures.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.4_Tips: Michele, a dedicated gamer, holds multiple world records across a variety of games.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.23_Tips: Michele loves cats, even though she hasn’t had one as a pet yet.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.26_Tips: Michele often emerges victorious with unexpected tactics, but she frequently ends up writing self-reflection reports for breaking the rules.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.56_Tips: Her colleagues often ask to borrow Fay. A people pleaser, Yvette agrees most of the time. But she always feels uneasy whenever Fay is away.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.68_Tips: Fuchsia sometimes acts childishly, though she is unaware of it, and others don't dare tell her...
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.64_Tips: Fuchsia favors food with a mild flavor that quickly replenishes energy, such as chocolate.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.18_Tips: Though your encounter was by chance, for Celestia, it was a meaningful inevitability.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.43_Tips: Although Kokona enjoys bustling places, she excels in solo operations.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.67_Tips: While she appears slim, Fuchsia is much stronger than you might think.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.2_Tips: Superstrings are individuals who are battle-hardened, constantly evolving, and possess special abilities.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.53_Tips: In crowds, Yvette goes into stealth to avoid potential social interactions. This tactic seems to be quite effective.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.60_Tips: Here's a secret about Kanami: she takes baths at home when she feels stressed.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.33_Tips: Behind her heavy firepower are trustworthy teammates and a belief that must be protected at all costs.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.62_Tips: Kanami has always wanted to sing a song she wrote herself.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.61_Tips: Kanami tends to hide her thoughts and emotions. She hopes you understand her vulnerability.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.58_Tips: Kanami was born to be an idol. Her looks, aura, and voice are all top-notch.

Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row16_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Since this is the first time we're having tea since becoming allies, it's important to have something delicious.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row10_PlayerOption2: Even as a dessert lover, I...
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I feel like we're missing something... Oh, we haven't ordered the drinks yet.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId105: The mousse cake and fruit tart also have great reviews...
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I know a great place we can get some afternoon tea.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId105: There's nothing wrong with having afternoon tea for dinner. I've done it a few times myself.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.RowNewRow_0_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Delete logs based on actual data.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Too many desserts? We can always order something else.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Just tell me what you want to eat. It's all on me.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId105: There are tons of flavors - mango, blueberry, matcha, chocolate, and more... Why don't we give them all a try?
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Ally, here is my contact information.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row5_PlayerOption1: I happen to be free, as well.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Today's one of those rare days I don't have any work to do. Would you like to have some tea together?
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row10_PlayerOption1: I'm a bit worried that I ruined my appetite...
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Their salmon sandwich and blueberry scones are delicious. They've become favorites of mine.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I made a reservation and got us a good window seat.

Audrey_105_Lv_3.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Last time, I went to an art exhibition.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row17_TextContent_FromPlayer: I can feel it... even without all those abstract paintings.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId105: But they enjoy a solid reputation in the industry.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId105: But this is abstract art. More specifically, it's abstract geometricism.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId105: You should have gotten it by now.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Interest is something that can be developed with time.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Ah... is it really not necessary?
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I felt as if I'd never really given you anything, so I got you ten pieces.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row9_PlayerOption2: Are you sure that it wasn't drawn with a compass and ruler?
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Most people seem to have this first impression. I can understand why.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row19_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Giving gifts is a tricky business.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row9_PlayerOption1: Can you tell me what these circles and squares mean...?
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId105: It may be the work of a new artist.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row16_PlayerOption1: When it comes to gifts, the feelings you express are what matters.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId105: My consultant showed me a super interesting painting. I thought you might like it, too.

Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId105: After we visited Café Reminiscence, I thought...
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId105: It's almost the raw flavor of coffee beans, tasting of unprocessed sourness and bitterness!
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId105: So... you prepared this for me?
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Hmm... It's got a unique name.
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I'm clearly enjoying the coffee right now.
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId105: No, I'm saying it's quite unique. I didn't know coffee with a taste this strong existed!
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I thought it'd be nice to have coffee every now and then.
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row5_1_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I didn't expect to receive a return gift so soon.
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row2_PlayerOption1: I've prepared a serving for you
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row12_PlayerOption1: You don't have to finish it...
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row2_PlayerOption2: This is the Astral Sanctuary's signature drink
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId105: The taste of the coffee is rather “special...”
Audrey_105_Lv_5.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Did you send me this box of ver.23.8.19.62 Starlight Coffee?

Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId105: “Where are the rest of my kind?” the unicorn ponders in sadness...
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId105: But... I just happen to have a storybook with me.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row16_TextContent_FromRoleId105: According to legends, a beautiful unicorn lives in this forest...
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId105: But I haven't been drinking much coffee as of late.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row8_PlayerOption2: I heard that counting sheep also helps
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId105: When drinking this type of coffee, one shouldn't be surprised if they stay awake for several days.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId105: No animals dare to approach it due to its uniqueness.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row21_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Ally, it's been a while since you've written back.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row12_PlayerOption2: I might just fall asleep before you do...
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId105: It was your suggestion, after all.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Ally, have you ever been troubled by insomnia?
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row23_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Amazing! Bedtime stories seem like a great way to deal with insomnia.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row12_PlayerOption1: Wait a moment... you want to tell me a bedtime story?
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId105: This is how you coax a child to sleep...
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I guess that counts as a success.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row8_PlayerOption1: Want to try a bedtime story?

Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row20_TextContent_FromRoleId105: See you later, then. Don't be late.

AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305020_From_Role132108: It's fine. Just another scolding from the almighty student council. It happens once a month. I'm used to it.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210731_From_Role107: No biggie! We won't have to fight for the best seats.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210742_From_Role107: The fireworks... they're just so beautiful!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214630_From_Role146: Now that the fireworks are over, does that mean the festival is too?
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212427_From_Role124: Just watching with my eyes isn’t enough. Time to bust out my special telescope!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212844_From_OtherRole: When I spotted it through the window, I thought it would be perfect for you.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212439_From_Role124: Watching such a grand fireworks display is like devouring all the street food on an entire block. Just pure satisfaction.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214618_From_Role146: I've been looking forward to this for so long...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009302003_From_Role101110: Come and check it out! Strinova Esports Club has been the Most Popular Student Club three years running! Hey, you there, ready to dive into the gaming world with us?
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210716_PlayerOption_ToRole107: The fireworks celebration does sound familiar...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210140_From_Role101: Seeing the sky made all the climbing worth it!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212441_PlayerOption_ToRole124: Another one for the books of magical metaphors...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210107_PlayerOption_ToRole101: Hold up, let me grab a translator…
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214607_From_Role146: Once the festival preparations are done, there should be a huge fireworks celebration. Why don't we watch it together?
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009304022_From_Role124111: Once I get into the Wright Institute of Technology, I'll invent even more amazing things!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210548_From_Role105: Oh well, this is enough. Otherwise, it’d be hard to cope once the feeling fades.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210109_From_Role101: Officer Michele finished her tasks at lightning speed and scored two front-row tickets to the fireworks festival!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210135_From_Role101: So we were heading to the rooftop...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210541_From_Role105: And we came through it all, right? Standing here with you under this vast night sky, watching the beautiful fireworks, feels like the perfect reward for all that "toughness.”
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214610_PlayerOption_ToRole146: Absolutely, I'd love to watch it with you!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305014_From_OtherRole: Please... help me... It's too crowded... I'm going to be pushed onto the stage...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009302006_From_Role101110: Where are my manners? I haven't introduced myself yet. My name is Michele. I'm a hardcore gamer, and the head of public relations of the Strinova Academy Esports Club.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210723_PlayerOption_ToRole107: I might not be able to help you find inspiration,
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009301010_From_Role105114: I've done way more than Bai Mo, and that's obvious to everyone.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210757_From_Role107: These memories are precious. It was the first time we watched the fireworks together, after all. That said... I still want you to have this for keepsake.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212407_From_Role124: I'm sure there will be many more, but I figured the first one should be enjoyed with my closest partner.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210136_From_Role101: If it wasn't for you, I would have just stringified and glided right up...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303007_From_Role112109: Excuse me! I've got more taiyaki!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210511_From_Role105: Speaking of which, Grove Enterprises is sponsoring the fireworks show. They usually save me a few front-row seats.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303017_From_OtherRole: By the way, Go-Home Club - that's a unique name. What does it mean? And why don't you have any staff members here?
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214627_From_Role146: Oh... so you've discovered my secret already?
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210108_From_Role101: Hey, hey, hey, don’t go! I'll talk normally! You know how all my P.U.S team members are helping with festival prep lately?
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210142_From_Role101: Huh? Is that so? Don't think for a second this means I don't love fireworks!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303019_From_Role112109: Studying is exhausting enough already. They will not take away my after-school time.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214640_From_Role146: Thanks for walking me home, Navigator.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212832_From_OtherRole: Thank you, Navigator. If you hadn't invited me here, I would’ve just admired this view from afar.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214619_PlayerOption_ToRole146: Let's go find the perfect spot!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212846_From_OtherRole: But thankfully... now my Spring Blessings feels complete.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210536_PlayerOption_ToRole105: It's been a tough year for you too, Audrey.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212432_From_Role124: A future where this world and your journey get better and better!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210758_From_Role107: This is a little something I made while searching for inspiration. It's yours now!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210545_From_Role105: Did we get here that quickly? The streets are so clear at night.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009304020_From_OtherRole: Is everything designed by members of your club? The thermal-sensing alarm and the medical drone are ready to go straight into production.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212425_From_Role124: These are the real deal... Wow... So beautiful!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210138_PlayerOption_ToRole101: That's the sweet reward after hard work!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009302008_From_Role101110: Here's our brochure. Please take a look. We've achieved great results in esports tournaments over the past few years!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214637_From_Role146: For me, that's as good as any celebration.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212828_From_OtherRole: This view... I've seen it before, in dreams...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210707_From_Role107: Now our little inspiration-gathering squad has assembled.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row611001502_From_Role128: The rich aroma of pastry and the fragrant smell of fillings are the perfect accompaniment to these celebrations, don't you agree?
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212837_From_OtherRole: They don't scare me. In fact, they push me forward. It's just... a bit lonely.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210508_PlayerOption_ToRole105: I'm a key part of the preparation efforts!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303002_From_OtherRole: A huge crowd has gathered over there... and everyone has taiyaki. Must be the Baking Club—I should check it out.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212833_From_OtherRole: These feelings, this perspective... I wouldn’t have them otherwise.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214628_From_Role146: In the days to come, this star will always be by your side.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212406_From_Role124: Sweet! That means I can officially rope you into catching the fireworks with me, right?
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210722_From_Role107: So does that mean... you can't join me on the inspiration hunt...? If you did then I guess it would count as cheating... We're gonna have to disband...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210118_From_Role101: I'll draw up our battle plan when I have some free time over the next few days. See you at the fireworks—be there or be square!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214626_PlayerOption_ToRole146: If that's the case, you're the shooting star that landed right next to me.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212409_PlayerOption_ToRole124: Hanging out with you, Kokona? Always!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210127_From_Role101: A hidden path? That's more like it, partner! Just lead the way!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212442_From_Role124: And hey, congrats! Since you were the first to watch the fireworks with me, I have a feeling you'll be getting a special good luck gift!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303008_Aside_AboutRole112109: (A rich fragrance wafts in from behind, laced with the warmth of freshly baked sweets, making the air deliciously inviting.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009301003_Aside_AboutRole128: (But today, I'm the citizen representative at Strinova Academy's open day, I have the important task of casting a decisive vote for the club competition... There's no way I'd miss this.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210543_Aside_AboutRole105: (Standing beside Audrey beneath the night sky, a serene and warm atmosphere fills the air.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212849_Aside_AboutRole128: (As I said my goodbyes to Lawine, I felt her gentle gaze linger on me. That feeling stayed with me long after I returned home.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210753_Aside_AboutRole107: (We quietly watched the night sky until the last firework fizzled out.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303022_From_OtherRole: (Why does she sound so proud of herself? But somehow... I feel convinced.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210504_Aside_AboutRole105: (So, after work, I find myself at Audrey's place as promised.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009304003_Aside_AboutRole112109: (I reach up and catch a small, lightweight airplane as it wobbles into my palm. It's hardly bigger than my hand, yet brimming with tiny components that scream the handiwork of a near-professional.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009302002_Aside_AboutRole105114: (A few students have approached me with flyers and conversations, but they all kept their distance. Perhaps it's because I'm an outsider...)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305009_Aside_AboutRole132108: (I have to admit—Ming's performance is phenomenal! Her fingers fly across the strings, sending electrifying melodies straight to the heart. Cheers rise wave upon wave, and the crowd just keeps growing.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009302010_From_OtherRole: (The Strinova Academy Esports Club is doing amazingly well! But why would such a popular club be at risk of being shut down?)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305008_Aside_AboutRole132108: (The guitarist who calls herself Ming... Why is she dressed like a delinquent? Is this her style?)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210103_Aside_AboutRole101: (Unfortunately, I missed them all because I was busy with festival preparations.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009304024_Aside_AboutRole124111: (After a delightful time with Kokona, I cast my vote before the next lecture kicks off.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009301004_Aside_AboutRole128: (This should be it. I was told someone from the student council would meet me here...)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009302001_Aside_AboutRole105114: (Because of the conspicuous seal, people stare at me wherever I go. It's making me a bit nervous.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210755_Aside_AboutRole107: (After the celebrations, I walked Maddelena back to her dorm.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305007_Aside_AboutRole132108: (They've set up a stage near the fountain, and it seems like a school band is performing. The vibe is pretty intense.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212802_Aside_AboutRole128: (During the hustle and bustle of preparing for the celebrations, I suddenly remembered that it had been a while since I last saw Lawine.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210502_Aside_AboutRole105: (During the busy festival preparations, I suddenly received a text from Audrey.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009301001_Aside_AboutRole128: (It's a cloudless, sunny day, perfect for an outing.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212803_Aside_AboutRole128: (She once mentioned her hometown's New Year traditions; they sounded a lot like the Spring Blessings...)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009301002_Aside_AboutRole128: (If it weren't for this special mission. I'd probably be having a picnic in the park with my friends.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303013_Aside_AboutRole112109: I carefully grab a piece, still warm, and give it a gentle blow before taking a bite. The fluffy crust melds with the rich red bean filling.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009304001_Aside_AboutRole112109: (As I wander down the tree-lined path, a sudden sting hits my head, kind of like getting pecked by an ostrich.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210519_Aside_AboutRole105: (And just like that, we made plans to watch the fireworks together.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305025_Aside_AboutRole132108: (Unsurprisingly, Ming doesn't give me a chance to explain. She grabs my arm and charges through the campus.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212428_Aside_AboutRole124: (I hold back a chuckle as Kokona fumbles around to make a "telescope" out of her fingers.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305010_From_OtherRole: (It's getting too crowded... If I move any further, I'll end up on stage!)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009304013_Aside_AboutRole124111: (A lecture just wrapped up at the Handicraft Club. Enthusiastic students swarm around the petite speaker, buzzing with excitement as they fire off questions.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303001_Aside_AboutRole101110: (Feeling proud as I cast my first vote. But with plenty of time left, there are still many clubs to explore.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212841_Aside_AboutRole128: (Lawine tilts her head back, gazing at the night sky. This time, there's a gentle smile in her eyes.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210702_Aside_AboutRole107: (I got a text from Maddelena asking me to visit her when I had the time.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210703_Aside_AboutRole107: (Things have been quite slow at the Astral Sanctuary lately, and with the festival approaching, I'll be clocking out earlier than usual.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210102_Aside_AboutRole101: (One day, I suddenly got bombarded with messages from Michele: phone calls, texts, and even in-game DMs...)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210756_Aside_AboutRole107: (As I was about to say goodbye, she shyly offered me something.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305002_Aside_AboutRole124111: (Suddenly, a powerful blast of music erupts, like thunder striking right at my forehead. It wakes me up instantly.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305001_Aside_AboutRole124111: (After walking along the tree-lined path for a while, the midday sun makes me feel drowsy.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009304004_Aside_AboutRole112109: (Then, despite the lack of wind, the tiny airplane takes off again on its own, pecks me once more, flutters its wings, and drifts away.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305016_Aside_AboutRole132108: (Before I know it, Ming yanks me onto the stage. A microphone is thrust into my hand, and I stand there, stunned, staring at the totally unfazed guitarist.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305004_Aside_AboutRole124111: (I look around, and everyone else seems just as startled. A few students, however, look excited and pick up their pace, jogging toward the source of the sound.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303014_Aside_AboutRole112109: (Sweet but not overwhelming, leaving a pleasant aftertaste. I'm no food critic, but this taiyaki is absolutely delicious!)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305026_Aside_AboutRole132108: (Looks like this over-the-top open day won’t be wrapping up anytime soon...)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214602_Aside_AboutRole146: (It's been a busy afternoon, but we finally managed to clear the last patient.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009305012_Aside_AboutRole132108: (Somehow, I've found myself in the spotlight. Engulfed by deafening cheers, escaping this crowd is a pipe dream... I just awkwardly smile and wave.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009304014_Aside_AboutRole124111: (Though it's clear some are just die-hard fans swooning over the speaker...)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210503_Aside_AboutRole105: (After a long preamble, it all boiled down to—"Can you drop by?")
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303004_Aside_AboutRole101110: (The booth buzzes with energy, but no staff in sight. Just a looping loudspeaker and an empty picnic basket.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212804_Aside_AboutRole128: (Maybe now's a good time to pay her a visit.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210704_Aside_AboutRole107: (Alright. I guess I should pay Maddelena a visit.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214638_Aside_AboutRole146: (I promised Celestia I’d spend more time with her and made a silent vow to do so.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210104_Aside_AboutRole101: (Once I had some free time, I decided to accept the invitation to check out the Cat Café.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303009_Aside_AboutRole112109: (The seemingly emotionless girl in front of me holds a nearly overflowing box of taiyaki with ease, her gaze sharp and condescending. She's definitely a tough one!)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009304019_Aside_AboutRole124111: (I cannot bring myself to refuse the girl's sincere invitation. With a curious mindset, I step into the tent. I'm instantly overwhelmed by everything inside.)
AVGEvent_Activity.Row1009303023_Aside_AboutRole112109: (As Fuchsia's determined gaze meets mine, my hand moves instinctively toward the voting box, casting my vote for the Go-Home Club.)

AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204031_From_OtherRole: “Lady Audrey's arguments were very convincing, and she provided unique insights into the coffee market. We cannot miss out on this potential partnership.”
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102010_From_Role105: ...But since it was your first offense, just don't let it happen again.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202047_From_Role105: ...But please, just give me a little of your feedback.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204045_From_Role105: ...Would you like to try it on? Only if you want to, of course.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102003_From_Role105: ...Hmpf! About time. You're five minutes late!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202033_From_Role105: ...Mm. I will remember your kindness. The Groves always pay their debts.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201027_From_Role105: Hmm... that could work! Ahem. We can quench our thirst while continuing to survey the public.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105101038_From_Role105: ...I didn't expect it to be this simple. This kind of communication skill isn't in my negotiation manual.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201050_From_Role105: I... I would never make such a misjudgment!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203015_From_Role105: ...I don't really want that to happen.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204015_From_Role105: ...And so, I haven't deviated from my original goal. There weren't any alternate motives behind my involvement with this café.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201042_From_OtherRole: Nowadays, we're just humble proprietors of this café... I still have a lot of customers to take care of, please excuse me!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201058_From_Role105: Sigh... I can't win when it comes to you! According to our contract, I cannot refuse the sincere invitation of my ally without a proper reason...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202055_From_Role105: ...T-truly? My standards are very strict. The quality barely passes the mark, but...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202041_From_Role105: ...How do we judge how sincere something is? Just how in the world are you supposed to make that kind of chocolate? Sure enough... I should just give up.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204013_From_Role105: ...Now is not the time to run around and hand out gifts. Our priority now should be to secure the café's financing.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203030_From_Role105: ...Listen carefully, now. This is a common negotiation tactic known as “the two unicorns.” One of us plays the white unicorn, representing emotion, while the other plays the black unicorn, representing logic.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203006_From_Role105: ...Isn't that a matter of course? It's just a few pieces of chocolate...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201032_From_Role105: ...I just said I don't drink coffee!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201047_From_Role105: “The Many Discourses” is my secret weapon. It's helped me close countless favorable deals, and I've never doubted its effectiveness.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102033_From_Role105: It's been a long time since I've played the violin... From my old home to Strinova, how many years has this instrument accompanied me?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202046_From_Role105: I'm not taking responsibility if it tastes bad!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201011_PlayerOption_ToRole105: You can't make friends like that!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102039_From_Role105: Keep moving forward, beyond the forest, other than the desert...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201007_From_Role105: That's right. True friendship guarantees a far stronger base of support than anything you can buy with money.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203062_From_Role105: You're right. The uniform taste of mass-produced coffee is a mark against its competitiveness. The automated production process can't produce the rich aroma that we expect from good coffee.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204021_From_OtherRole: Long time no see! I just got a response from the Committee...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203008_From_OtherRole: Welcome! What would you two like today?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204003_From_Role105: Why haven't we received a response yet?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102028_From_Role105: Let me be clear. I-I just want to practice my violin...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203011_From_OtherRole: They've taken most of our customers. We've only been getting a handful of regulars with a taste for artisanal coffee over the past few weeks.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203022_From_Role105: What the Committee is looking for is simple - “new ideas and artisanal craft.”
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204119_From_Role105: Since he invited us here, I guess the shopkeeper must have gotten some news from the Committee, right?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204053_From_Role105: B-But I've enjoyed getting along with you during our time together. So, thank you...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203013_From_Role105: But for some reason, the idea of not being able to enjoy this “sincere” coffee bothers me...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203060_From_OtherRole: The market is clear - artisanal coffee is on the way out! Compared to coffee made through automated production methods, it loses out in volume and price!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102037_From_Role105: But at least for now... Ally, would you mind listening to me play a song?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105101019_From_Role105: Y-You could be a friend of the Groves...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202058_PlayerOption_ToRole105: Why are you so hung up on quality?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203018_From_Role105: You too? ...Indeed, we discovered this coffee together.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105101025_PlayerOption_ToRole105: You didn't sound like a friend...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201005_From_Role105: All you need to do is help me negotiate. Did I tell you that I've mastered every technique written in “The Many Discourses” and have a 100% closing rate?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105101012_PlayerOption_ToRole105: You want me as your business partner?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201006_PlayerOption_ToRole105: Are you trying to make friends through negotiation?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105101017_From_Role105: I find your attitude... somewhat unexpected. The Grove family is reputable and respected in both the business and finance sectors. I don't see a single reason why you would say no.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203028_From_Role105: That's a good attitude. Confidence is the key to a successful negotiation.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201009_PlayerOption_ToRole105: Your understanding is a bit off...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102030_PlayerOption_ToRole105: You must be a great violinist!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201045_PlayerOption_ToRole105: Let's try a skill other than negotiation!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201064_From_Role105: My judgment tells me that this coffee is unmatched by most teas on the market! I didn't expect to find such an incredible hand-brewed drink in this small shop.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105101034_From_Role105: I would like to reiterate that the friendship I desire is one that's long-lasting and stable. You will be my most valuable ally. Your wishes and demands will also be respected to the greatest extent possible as reflected in the contract.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203048_From_Role105: I'd recommend you start by sampling Café Reminiscence's signature drink - coffee cherry wine.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202003_From_Role105: I wonder where I'm going wrong. I've never made a mistake in the business world...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202029_From_Role105: Making chocolates was never part of our contract, so you can stop anytime. This is my battle at the end of the day...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201043_From_Role105: Another failed negotiation... I-I don't believe it!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202022_From_Role105: I-It's just a few pieces of chocolate. Hardly anything I can't handle!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105101018_From_Role105: Darn it. I have never failed a business negotiation... Are you sure you don't want to reconsider? I'm hoping that...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204024_From_OtherRole: Uh... how should I put this? I really didn't expect...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204008_PlayerOption_ToRole105: We came here to make friends...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203052_From_Role105: When did we stop serving coffee? How long has it been since the family got together for a tea party?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204051_From_Role105: Saying that all of a sudden...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203010_From_OtherRole: It's a long story... The cat café nearby, Paw Pledge, came out with a new type of coffee. The production process is fully automated, so they can pump out coffee at low prices.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201012_From_Role105: Hmpf! What did I just say? I've never lost a negotiation!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105101020_PlayerOption_ToRole105: Business cooperation is not in my area of expertise.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203046_From_Role105: The choice between investments and investors has always been a two-way street. In a roundabout way, you two and my partner over here are also competing.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203019_From_Role105: Um... don't misunderstand. What I mean is... discovering this great coffee was an important outcome of our alliance!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204018_From_Role105: Ah! A message from the shopkeeper.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102056_From_Role105: Ah! There was one more thing that I have to say! Please listen carefully. I'm not going to repeat myself...
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202051_From_Role105: Hey, I don't want to think about these chocolates anymo...!!
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203077_From_Role105: Mm. It was a gift from my parents when I was young.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202008_From_Role105: The Grove family has an old tradition. Every time the family meets, we exchange handmade chocolates with each other to convey our feelings.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201008_From_Role105: The way I see it, making friends and negotiating are the same thing. In essence, both are a struggle to earn someone's respect.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102048_From_Role105: At some point, wearing the unicorn medal, you've become like family to me.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203053_From_Role105: As time marched on, technological advances and automated production have gradually pushed out artisanal craft. Our family went through much, too.
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105101011_From_Role105: Based on our previous cooperation, I am interested in establishing a long-term partnership with you. Together, we will be unstoppable!

AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204017_Aside_AboutRole105: (It was clear that sentimentality was what truly drove her to save the café.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102051_Aside_AboutRole105: (The lonely unicorn disappeared. What remained was the girl, her eyebrows furrowed as she continued to play.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201016_Aside_AboutRole105: (And so the inspired negotiator applied their unique insights to try and make friends with one stranger after another.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102040_Aside_AboutRole105: (As Audrey hummed, the last unicorn from the fairy tale galloped in the direction of the flying notes.)
