HelpTipsUI.9_Content:
<CommonRulePopUp_18_Blod>Earning Union Merit and EXP</>
1. Play matches with your Union to earn Union Merit. The amount depends on the mode and match outcome.
2. Participate in tournaments to earn Union Merit. The amount depends on the match outcome.
3. If negative behavior is detected in a match, Union Merit will not be awarded.
4. Any Union Merit earned will convert to Union EXP at a 1:1 ratio.

<CommonRulePopUp_18_Blod>Weekly Union EXP Limit</>
Union EXP earned each week is capped. Once the limit is reached, no more Union EXP can be earned.
Resets every Monday at 6:00 AM.

<CommonRulePopUp_18_Blod>Level Rewards</>
1. Earn the required amount of Union Merit in your current Union to claim level rewards.
2. Memory Sequences, Dimension Gift Boxes, and EXP Bonus Cards are one-time rewards. Once claimed, they cannot be reclaimed by switching Unions.
3. Medals, player cards, and cases are Union privilege rewards and cannot be used if you leave the Union.

<CommonRulePopUp_18_Blod>Union Inactivity Penalty</>
If all Union members have been offline for more than 7 days, Union EXP will be deducted daily at 6:00 AM until a member logs in.
HelpTipsUI.8_Content:
<CommonRulePopUp_18_Blod>Leader Rights</>
The leader can approve members, remove members, transfer leadership, and edit Union details.

<CommonRulePopUp_18_Blod>Deputy Leader Rights</>
The leader can appoint up to 2 deputy leaders.
Deputies can approve and remove members.

<CommonRulePopUp_18_Blod>Automatic Leader Transfer</>
If the leader is inactive for more than 14 days, leadership will automatically transfer to an active Union member.
HelpTipsUI.15_Content:
{1} Rules:
1. After purchasing a gift box, it will automatically open.
2. Every item in the gift box has different drop rates.
3. Each item has a "limited obtainable count." Items with zero count left won't be drawn again, increasing the drop rates for other items of the same Quality.
4. If you already own unique items from the gift box, you will not receive duplicates.
5. When all items are drawn, the gift box converts to {2} *{3}.
6. Item drop rates are shown up to two decimal places.
HelpTipsUI.16_Content:
{1} Rules:
1. The gift box opens automatically upon purchase.
2. Each item in the gift box has its own drop rate.
3. Every item has a limited "obtainable count." Once an item's count reaches zero, it will no longer drop, and the drop rates for other items of the same Quality will increase.
4. When all items of a certain Quality are obtained, drop rates for items of other Qualities will increase.
5. If you already own a unique item from the gift box, you won't receive it again.
6. Once all items have been drawn, the gift box will be converted into {2} *{3}.
7. Drop rates are displayed to two decimal places.
HelpTipsUI.36_Content: Second, defuse the device before the timer runs out.
HelpTipsUI.43_Content: Also, the payload allows for wall-sticking on all sides.
HelpTipsUI.34_Content: Victory is only achieved when the bomb detonates or all enemies are eliminated.
HelpTipsUI.19_Content: In the Final Showdown, become the "Bobblehead King" to boost your attributes, but you can only use melee weapons and respawning is disabled for everyone.
HelpTipsUI.18_Content: Dealing damage, defeating enemies, or healing teammates will make your head grow larger.
HelpTipsUI.47_Content: During the match, both Superstrings and Crystallines can receive supplies and draw cards.
HelpTipsUI.31_Content: As the attacker, you need to cover the teammate carrying the bomb as they enter the bomb site and plant the bomb.
HelpTipsUI.35_Content: If you're a defender, remember these two winning tips: First, eliminate all enemies before they plant the bomb.
HelpTipsUI.17_Content: The match begins with three teams of five players each.
HelpTipsUI.46_Content: At the start, 3 players are randomly chosen as Crystallines, and any defeated Superstrings will immediately mutate into Crystallines.
HelpTipsUI.21_Content: At the start of the match, several players are randomly chosen as Bomb Carriers.
HelpTipsUI.27_Content: Don't panic when you see duplicate Superstring Agents; it's a feature of the game.
HelpTipsUI.11_Content: Servers determine your current network node. To ensure a stable connection and optimal gameplay, you can't switch servers frequently.
HelpTipsUI.32_Content: If the teammate carrying the bomb goes down, it will be dropped at their current location.
HelpTipsUI.25_Content: Team Arena tests your team's strength, where you'll fight alongside your teammates.
HelpTipsUI.50_Content: Crystalline wins by infecting all Superstrings.
HelpTipsUI.48_Content: Crystallines can respawn after death; however, only a Ninjato can eliminate them permanently.
HelpTipsUI.45_Content: In Outbreak, Superstrings must work together to fight off the infected Crystallines.
HelpTipsUI.28_Content: Finally, don't forget to tell your teammate that the team's Victory Objective is to defeat a specified number of enemies quickly.
HelpTipsUI.38_Content: The first team to reach the target score wins.
HelpTipsUI.39_Content: Escort requires teamwork, with attackers and defenders battling over the payload.
HelpTipsUI.37_Content: Also, after playing the set number of rounds, both sides will switch roles.
HelpTipsUI.24_Content: Survivors earn points each round, and the player with the highest total points wins.
HelpTipsUI.22_Content: Bomb Carriers can pass the bomb to opponents through melee attacks.
HelpTipsUI.23_Content: The bomb will explode after some time or at the end of the round, blowing up the player carrying it.
HelpTipsUI.30_Content: Understanding the map layout, bomb sites, and key routes is your first step to mastering the game.
HelpTipsUI.29_Content: Demolition missions demand teamwork, with attackers and defenders clashing over bomb placement.
HelpTipsUI.26_Content: Teaming up is a good idea, as lone players can easily get overwhelmed.
HelpTipsUI.20_Content: The team with the highest number of winning rounds achieves victory.
HelpTipsUI.33_Content: Stay alert after planting the bomb; don't celebrate too early.
HelpTipsUI.49_Content: Superstring wins if at least one member survives until the end.
HelpTipsUI.44_Content: Master these rules, and victory will be yours.
HelpTipsUI.40_Content: Attackers must escort the payload along the route to the destination in time.
HelpTipsUI.41_Content: Defenders must intercept the payload and eliminate enemies in its path.
HelpTipsUI.42_Content: Note that the attackers can only push the payload when they stay close to it.

HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId146: So, what’s your plan for the rest of the day?
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row4_PlayerOption2: I didn't realize Astral Sanctuary had branches.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row9_PlayerOption2: I'll wander around for a bit.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Sure, feel free to drop by anytime. The door unlocks with a facial scan.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId146: In that case, enjoy your stroll, Navigator.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Haha, that was my exact reaction when I first got the map too.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId146: I’ve sent the map to you as well.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId146: If I'm not around, I'm probably attending to a patient, so you might need to wait a bit.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId146: I tend to spend more time at this branch, helping the people in this community.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Star Street, East 198th District, Strian. This is where the Astral Sanctuary branch is located.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId146: You'd be surprised; it’s not as bustling as Area 88, but the quiet here has its own charm that I really enjoy.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId146: If there's anything you need, don't hesitate to ask.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row9_PlayerOption1: I'll pop by to check out your branch.
HuiXing_146_Lv_0.Row4_PlayerOption1: Now I won't take the wrong train again.

HuiXing_146_Lv_1.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId146: By "latest," I mean I create a unique blend every day.
HuiXing_146_Lv_1.Row3_PlayerOption1: Actually, I don't really drink coffee.
HuiXing_146_Lv_1.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId146: By tweaking these meticulously, I can enrich the flavor, even making it taste like cola if you wish!
HuiXing_146_Lv_1.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Since you've come all the way here, would you like to try my latest brew of Starlight Coffee?
HuiXing_146_Lv_1.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId146: I'll do my best to show you the charm of Starlight Coffee.
HuiXing_146_Lv_1.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Do you have any particular preferences?
HuiXing_146_Lv_1.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Since I'm managing Astral Sanctuary all on my own, coffee is the only option I can offer...
HuiXing_146_Lv_1.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId146: There's a lot that goes into a cup of coffee. You need to think about the water volume, grind size, extraction rate, and more...
HuiXing_146_Lv_1.Row8_PlayerOption1: Wow, now you've got my attention!

HuiXing_146_Lv_10.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId146: I'm sure it’ll all work out.
HuiXing_146_Lv_10.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId146: After tons of prep work, it's finally happening!
HuiXing_146_Lv_10.Row8_PlayerOption1: Haha, fingers crossed the weather’s perfect that night.
HuiXing_146_Lv_10.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Yep! We’re planning a public stargazing event at Astral Sanctuary.
HuiXing_146_Lv_10.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId146: So, I hope you can take a well-deserved break.
HuiXing_146_Lv_10.RowNewRow_0_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Delete logs based on actual data.
HuiXing_146_Lv_10.Row2_PlayerOption1: You seem to be in a good mood.
HuiXing_146_Lv_10.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId146: It's been pretty cloudy lately, but as long as there's wind tonight, we should have clear skies.
HuiXing_146_Lv_10.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId146: And I know I’ve asked you for a lot of help before...

HuiXing_146_Lv_2.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId146: The V23.8.19.62 significantly improves upon the overly mild taste of V14.3.2.44.
HuiXing_146_Lv_2.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId146: But for some reason, everyone keeps politely turning down my offer to try it...
HuiXing_146_Lv_2.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId146: I've perfected the latest version of Starlight Coffee V23.8.19.62.
HuiXing_146_Lv_2.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Um, there's something I need to tell you...
HuiXing_146_Lv_2.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Oh... it's the first time someone agreed so readily! I knew I could count on you!
HuiXing_146_Lv_2.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Great, let's meet in the canteen after work!
HuiXing_146_Lv_2.Row14_PlayerOption1: It's no big deal, I'd love to try it.
HuiXing_146_Lv_2.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId146: I've added a bunch of real ingredients, like fragrant mint, white orchid, jasmine tea, oat flakes, even tuna.
HuiXing_146_Lv_2.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId146: So, I was really hoping you could...
HuiXing_146_Lv_2.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId146: It took me a lot of effort, and it'd be such a shame if no one could appreciate it...
HuiXing_146_Lv_2.Row8_PlayerOption2: What's up with that ridiculously long version number?

HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Don't tell me you're in on it too?
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId146: You're not supposed to hear yourself talking in your sleep, right?
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Three all-nighters in a row... Definitely not doing that again...
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId146: I'm asking because I just had a super weird moment.
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId146: And you are definitely helping me out with it!
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Do I often talk in my sleep?
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId146: But during my nap, I actually did hear myself...
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Eh? Kokona was here? She probably saw me napping and decided not to wake me.
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row13_PlayerOption2: You know what they say about snitches...
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Haha, I knew it! She definitely recorded me sleep-talking.
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Eh? Don't tell me it's V23.8.19.62? Ugh...
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Hmm... Did she have a mischievous grin on her face when she was leaving?
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row16_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Mmm... Looks like I'll have to give Kokona a special "welcome" the next time she visits.
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.RowNewRow_0_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Delete logs based on actual data.
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row2_PlayerOption2: Yeah, you keep repeating Starlight Coffee version numbers.
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row2_PlayerOption1: Yeah, you keep repeating dessert names.
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row13_PlayerOption1: Yep, she was smirking and fiddling with a recorder.
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId146: Thinking about it now... It's so strange...
HuiXing_146_Lv_6.Row10_PlayerOption1: By the way, Kokona dropped by at Astral Sanctuary earlier.

IdCard.31000033_Desc: Area 88 is where the largest financial system of Strinova is located.
IdCard.31001034_Desc: "Why do I wear red? Because it brings good luck! The closer you are to me, the luckier you will be!"
IdCard.31000181_Desc: “People need shelter and resources to survive, but also the bells and sunlight to awaken the soul.”
IdCard.31001112_Desc: "In the name of the student council, these activities are forbidden at school."
IdCard.31001081_Desc: "Surely you saw the troubled expression on the guest's face?"
IdCard.31001121_Desc: What are you afraid of? Battle, farewell, or me turning it all upside down?
IdCard.31000191_Desc: "The pioneers say the brilliance from the depths of string energy resembles sunrise, bringing long-lost splendor to humanity."
IdCard.31001113_Desc: "Hold those screams—let them loose when I hit the stage!"
IdCard.31000184_Desc: “As her deformed body falls into eternal decay, she draws the corrupted souls into the sea of flowers nevertheless.”
IdCard.31000193_Desc: “Silent is the ancient temple, yet the footsteps of pioneers and successors echo throughout.”
IdCard.31000154_Desc:
"Meow! Meow, meow, meow!"
Pawtector seems to be training Mighty Meow, who is not so good at video games.
IdCard.31001120_Desc: “They called me the Grim Reaper before I became a countess. She is ever so unpredictable. Nonetheless, this is how I received an invitation.”
IdCard.31000186_Desc: “She... It stands on top of the tower, bringing down endless fear and confusion.”
IdCard.31000185_Desc: “If you find it, please listen carefully. What's sealed is not a mad desire but a trembling heart.”
IdCard.31001065_Desc: “Please let us know if anything is not to your liking.”
IdCard.31001107_Desc: "If you wish, I'd cross time and space to meet you."
IdCard.31001066_Desc: “I'll come visit often, if only for the amazing tea.”
IdCard.31001115_Desc: Hope the teacher doesn't catch me trying to build a mega toy in class!
IdCard.31000189_Desc: “We had the purest intentions, but the tower eventually led to opposite ends.”
IdCard.31000001_Desc: Making contact and observing are only the first steps. It's up to you to make the next move, Navigator.
IdCard.31001105_Desc: "Wishing everyone a bountiful year of wealth and prosperity... Wait, the lucky beast? It's this little one on my shoulder, of course!"
IdCard.31001114_Desc: "Every season at school has its treasures, like the cherry blossoms now."
IdCard.31000151_Desc:
“Welcome to The Hometown. How would you like your egg cooked?”
Shows like this seem to be quite popular at the restaurant called The Hometown.
IdCard.31001118_Desc: “Too long has the Castle of Eternal Night slumbered. It is time to awaken it. Will you take part in the grand revival?”
IdCard.31000190_Desc: “The bear will protect you, though mainly the land beneath you.”
IdCard.31001116_Desc: Maybe I'll just head straight home from here... Wait, no... I'll get in trouble for that....
IdCard.31001097_Desc: Delightfully cute and tasty omelette rice!
IdCard.31001106_Desc: "Captivated by my performance? That's only natural."
IdCard.31000188_Desc: “Why? I don't know. I'm just a Mighty Meow.”
IdCard.31000147_Desc: "Eh? It's so strange. You obviously followed the recipe step by step...!"
IdCard.31001119_Desc: “There's no need to be afraid. Though I often have my eyes covered, I am not blind. I simply choose not to witness more suffering...”
IdCard.31001064_Desc: “I haven't got the munchies. I need a full belly before I can fight!”
IdCard.31000192_Desc: “It's a beautiful place. Once everything settles down, let's look for rainbows.”
IdCard.31000180_Desc: “Youth, courage, a world to explore. We had everything, our hope undying.”
IdCard.31000187_Desc: “Fragrance is more than just a scent. It signifies a symbol, a story, a memory, the formation of life and soul.”
IdCard.31002002_Desc:
"Have you ever truly looked at the starry sky?"
"I heard there is a unique star for everyone, waiting alone in the universe, hoping someone would gaze at it."
"If one day you see an unusual light in the sky, that's probably your star winking at you."
"Where is my star? Well... that's a secret."

The girl never stops chasing the night sky.
Through countless nights under the stars, she patiently waits for that one star in the vast galaxy to reveal itself.
One day, the star winks at her.
And the entire night sky changes its colors.
IdCard.31002005_Desc:
【“Whether it's going on an adventure or simply sleeping in, one must do what they love the most on a rare off day!”
Having finished a day's work, Kokona changes into comfortable clothes and lays down.

Next to her are stacks of boxes and all kinds of items.
Among them are memorabilia she has not had time to organize and essential tools for her future explorations.
“Come on. Don't just stand there. Help me out.”】
IdCard.31002007_Desc:
“It's not that I don't like going out...”
The girl shyly pulls down the brim of her bear hoodie. “It's just that there are too many people outside, and it's noisy... At home, I have Fay, blankets, and endless chilled drinks...”
“I think it's really nice to just stay at home... W-Wouldn't you agree?”
IdCard.31002009_Desc:
【“Would you like another taiyaki? Or a sweet shark?”
Sitting on a floor mat, Fuchsia extends her hands to me, offering a piece of taiyaki in one and a sweet shark in the other - a dilemma of sweetness.
Although it is really tempting, I have already had too many sweet snacks today. I swallow as I firmly refuse Fuchsia's offer.
“Suit yourself.” Fuchsia shrugs before taking a huge bite, licking the crumbs from the corner of her mouth. Then, she stretches lazily and sprawls on the floor.
“This is how you should spend your holiday.”】
IdCard.31002004_Desc:
【“What flower is this? It's an orchid.”
The floral fragrance of the tea wafts from the cups in front of Lawine and you.
The pale petals unfold in your cup of tea.
You notice that a similar flower is embroidered on her clothes.

“Orchids only bloom in spring, a season far too short in this world.”
As she sips some tea, the girl in front of you smiles, barely perceptible.
For her, this brief respite from all her responsibilities and duties is her spring.】
IdCard.31002003_Desc:
【After playing a violin piece, Audrey sits next to you.
“Why do you still look so gloomy when I'm with you?”
“What are you worried about? The test we have to face? Or the inevitable collapse?”

She pours two cups of black tea and places one before of you.
“Let go of all the troubles. Let us toast to hardship and... this world.”
As the cups touch, producing a crisp sound,  the girl smiles confidently.】
IdCard.31002008_Desc:
【As an idol, Kanami enjoys spending time on makeup and styles.
Whether it's a natural look or an elegant stage look, Kanami excels at putting them on, skillfully applying any makeup products.
As Kanami finishes her makeup, she draws a cute mark on the mirror with her lipstick.
“Navigator, will you be colored by my hues?”】
IdCard.31002001_Desc:
Super gamer Michele has many stylish casual outfits. Of course, our cat lover prefers this cute cat-themed outfit, whether for its comfiness or the adorable kitty colors.

"Cats show their belly when they want to be friendly and feeling safe." The girl says, smiling.

Michele has changed her flashy gamer gear into a cute girl's outfit. Is the cat girl trying to tell you something with that change?
IdCard.31001002_Desc:
Having become a frontline investigator, Michele carries with her the will of her father. When a badge number is reactivated, the pitiful criminals better tremble in fear, for the successor of the White Tiger will defeat every single one of them.

“Listen up! I have you surrounded! Surrender now!” Michele once intimidated suspects like this during operations.
And she kept her word, singlehandedly arresting over a dozen suspects.
"I thought I wouldn't see the light of day again. Was she going to devour us like a wild tiger?" a criminal recalls, trembling in fear.
IdCard.31000178_Desc: 【The shark in the tank does not realize its freedom is lost, nor does it feel any pain. People pity it for losing the dignity of a predator, but the shark does not care.】
IdCard.31001001_Desc:
The royal swordswoman, enchanting as a rose, gazes into the distance.
She sees nothing but carnage and rivers of blood.
The rose-decorated sword pierces an enemy's heart.
The rose is dyed in blood's hue; shadows cast wide their pall.
Her mind, like the breeze, wanders far, unconfined by any wall.
“For you alone, the flowers unveil their bloom; should they fade, what sorrow calls?”
IdCard.31000112_Desc: The start of all joys and sorrows.
IdCard.31000108_Desc: Would you like a cup of tea?
IdCard.31000002_Desc: The anchor of the world. The beacon of the city. A shining tower of string energy.

Outside...

IdCard.31000007_Desc: The sky is filled with inspiration. Can you not see?
IdCard.31001013_Desc: In the endless expanse of the sky, I wander solo, my song soaring freely.
IdCard.31001061_Desc: She has traversed every corner of this land, and from now on, she will tread the skies.
