SequenceDialogue.Row9804021_TextContext_Role133: There's more than one group of AI guards. We need to eliminate them all, so don't let up!
SequenceDialogue.Row9801066_TextContext_Role124: It's a P-4 model, remember? We've trained for this.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804003_TextContext_Role133: ———— (cutting out) Lawine? Can you... hear me? Lawine?
SequenceDialogue.Row9800005_TextContext_Player: A “Utopia” where eternal life was possible, all thanks to the power of superstrings.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801050_TextContext_Role124: Not good, the control center's been breached.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804030_TextContext_Role133: No good, enemy fire is too dense. Take evasive action, do not get bogged down.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804025_TextContext_Role133: Stay vigilant. There will be two more garages up ahead. Let's push on.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801044_TextContext_Role124: But, since you already have this determination, stay true to your resolve until the day we conquer the collapse syndrome.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801018_TextContext_Role128: No, Komos Tower is heavily guarded. This time, we'll split up.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801001_TextContext_Role128: I've waited far too long for this moment. There's no turning back now.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804006_TextContext_Role128: The power of P.U.S' defense system - you have to see it to believe it.
SequenceDialogue.Row9800003_TextContext_Player: The wretched awaited rescue in the frozen wastes.
SequenceDialogue.Row9800007_TextContext_Player: In this new era, humans became like gods.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801042_TextContext_Role124: If peace is our final goal, it will surely be a long journey.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801057_TextContext_Role101: Yvette, keep working on the research. Kokona and I will go and handle The Scissors!
SequenceDialogue.Row9801078_TextContext_Role124: Yvette, The Scissors' target is the crystal!
SequenceDialogue.Row9801029_TextContext_Role131: The collapse results in the degradation of the string sequence
SequenceDialogue.Row9801032_TextContext_Role131: But this experiment iterates on past purification methods. Using a black box approach to isolate the observer and prevent collapse.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801035_TextContext_Role131: If they are below three Planck constants
SequenceDialogue.Row9801011_TextContext_Role132: Just put me out of my misery!
SequenceDialogue.Row9801076_TextContext_Role124: Keep disarming it, I’m heading to support Yvette!
SequenceDialogue.Row9804029_TextContext_Role133: We'll come through the sides. Keep your eye out for any ambushes.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804018_TextContext_Role133: Excellent work, Lawine. Ahead of you is the Comos AI Garage. All the AI perimeter guards come from here. Ming will find a way to hijack the guards - that will be your opportunity to strike.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801033_TextContext_Role131: Using a black box approach to isolate the observer and prevent collapse
SequenceDialogue.Row9804016_TextContext_Role133: There's no conventional way forward. Our databases show that the only way to progress is through stringification.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801072_TextContext_Role124: The Scissors are stalling us with this bomb. They're buying time…
SequenceDialogue.Row9801008_TextContext_Role128: New patients again? More memory wipes and reconstructions...
SequenceDialogue.Row9801036_TextContext_Role131: We can consider achieving 100% theoretical purity possible
SequenceDialogue.Row9801067_TextContext_Role101: But the programming's different, each set has unique logic…
SequenceDialogue.Row9801005_TextContext_Role128: Hm, it's time. Those two should be here by now.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801030_TextContext_Role131: So, achieving a perfect string sequence configuration was previously impossible
SequenceDialogue.Row9800006_TextContext_Player: In Strinova, there was no hunger, no cold, and no pain.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804009_TextContext_Role133: We've mapped out the terrain and plotted an ingress route. The program will provide a holographic projection in your eyes. Follow the path - you've only got one shot.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804032_TextContext_Role133: Coordinates 78,312. Vertical distance of 33. An excellent tactical position.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801007_TextContext_Role137: It took a while to calm down the new collapse syndrome patients.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801040_TextContext_Role101: Nobody would have to lose their precious memories anymore...
SequenceDialogue.Row9801012_TextContext_Role137: Relax, once we extract those high-purity crystals, we'll find a way back to Earth for sure!
SequenceDialogue.Row9801010_TextContext_Role132: If one day, I start experiencing collapse syndrome...
SequenceDialogue.Row9801039_TextContext_Role101: If we can truly cure collapse syndrome, maybe my father could remember who I am. Nobody would have to lose their precious memories anymore... Maybe even The Scissors would come to accept this world.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801054_TextContext_Role124: Scholars are meant to focus on their research. But since The Scissors wants a fight... Michele, today’s your first real combat lesson.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801027_TextContext_Role124: Even if we reach the anticipated level, it would only slow it down
SequenceDialogue.Row9801041_TextContext_Role101: Maybe even The Scissors would come to accept this world.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801025_TextContext_Role101: Could it mean there’s hope for curing the Collapse Syndrome?
SequenceDialogue.Row9801028_TextContext_Role131: When the crystal transitions to an eigenstate, the collapse results in the degradation of the string sequence
SequenceDialogue.Row9801016_TextContext_Role128: Hopefully, crystals of this purity will open the space rift
SequenceDialogue.Row9801024_TextContext_Role101: Instructor Kokona, if we succeed this time, could it mean there’s hope for curing the Collapse Syndrome?
SequenceDialogue.Row9801063_TextContext_Role101: Instructor Kokona, what’s our next move?
SequenceDialogue.Row9801013_TextContext_Role137: We'll find a way back to Earth for sure!
SequenceDialogue.Row9801014_TextContext_Role128: I just got a message from Meredith. P.U.S has refined the purification method at Komos Tower, and they’re almost done. Hopefully, crystals of this purity will open the space rift.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801020_TextContext_Role128: I'll distract P.U.S, and you take the chance to grab the crystals.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804013_TextContext_Role133: I can tell that you're getting the hang of this place.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804026_TextContext_Role132: Report. I've lost control over the AI guards!
SequenceDialogue.Row9804019_TextContext_Role132: Report. Ming has struck the Comos defense center. The system should be offline for around thirty minutes. Over and out.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804014_TextContext_Role137: Report. Kanami has made it to the Comos control room and should be disabling the alarm system within ten seconds. Over and out.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801006_TextContext_Role137: Sorry we're late. It took a while to calm down the new collapse syndrome patients.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801065_TextContext_Role124: Disarm the bomb, I’ll cover you.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804028_TextContext_Role133: Lawine, the guards are back online. The enemy's location is unknown. Let's start by determining the enemy's coordinates.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804005_TextContext_Role133: If everything has gone to plan, you should be inside the Comos defense system.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804034_TextContext_Role133: The amount of damage is somewhat lower than expected. Excellent! The Comos Center Console should be right in front of you.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801053_TextContext_Role131: The purification process is almost complete
SequenceDialogue.Row9804023_TextContext_Role133: Attack! This should be the last of them.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801056_TextContext_Role101: Yvette, keep working on the research. Kokona and I will go and handle The Scissors!
SequenceDialogue.Row9804039_TextContext_Role124: The enemy has bypassed the defense system and reached the center console.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801031_TextContext_Role131: Achieving a perfect string sequence configuration was previously impossible.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804007_TextContext_Role133: Our time is running out. I'll guide you through. Ming and Kanami will assist from the outside.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804035_TextContext_Role132: Ming has made successful contact with Kanami.
SequenceDialogue.Row9800001_TextContext_Player: The moon had been forever buried in an endless night.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801062_TextContext_Role124: It's too quiet... did we miss something?
SequenceDialogue.Row9804020_TextContext_Role133: Copy that. Over to you, Lawine.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801015_TextContext_Role128: P.U.S has refined the purification method at Komos Tower and they’re almost done
SequenceDialogue.Row9801026_TextContext_Role124: It's not that simple. Considering the current progression of the Collapse Syndrome, even if we reach the anticipated level, it would only slow it down.
SequenceDialogue.Row9800002_TextContext_Player: The sea beat and swelled, expanding its tendrils across the world.
SequenceDialogue.Row9800008_TextContext_Player: But to humanity, was eternal life more “dream” or “fantasy?”
SequenceDialogue.Row9801037_TextContext_Role101: 100%... If that's possible, my father might...
SequenceDialogue.Row9804024_TextContext_Role133: The target has been annihilated. Not bad.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801023_TextContext_Role124: It looks like the purification process is almost done.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801068_TextContext_Role124: Different programming? They meticulously altered the code, yet didn’t bother guarding the bomb site... this is unlike them.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801055_TextContext_Role124: Michele, today’s your first real combat lesson
SequenceDialogue.Row9801075_TextContext_Role124: Damn it! Keep disarming it, I’m heading to support Yvette!
SequenceDialogue.Row9800004_TextContext_Player: What they found instead was a new world - Strinova.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801034_TextContext_Role131: Taking into account quantum fluctuations in the purification chamber, if they are below three Planck constants, we can consider achieving 100% theoretical purity possible.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801070_TextContext_Role124: Yet didn’t bother guarding the bomb site... this is unlike them.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804017_TextContext_Role133: As for here... If my calculations are correct, you'll be able to use the air current to give your jump an extra push! Just remember to keep stringifying!
SequenceDialogue.Row9801052_TextContext_Role131: Fay is worried. The purification process is almost complete.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801038_TextContext_Role131: Fay believes that, in theory, it’s possible to cure collapse syndrome.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801080_TextContext_Role131: Fay, did you hear that? Four o'clock...
SequenceDialogue.Row9801009_TextContext_Role132: If you ask me, I don't want to go through either collapse syndrome or restoration. If one day, I start experiencing collapse syndrome... Just put me out of my misery!
SequenceDialogue.Row9804031_TextContext_Role133: Calculations show that you'll have an injury chance of over 60% in a head-on confrontation. Modify the assault plan and find a new route.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801058_TextContext_Role124: Stick with me. Let's move out!
SequenceDialogue.Row9804002_TextContext_Role128: It's good that we were prepared.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804012_TextContext_Role133: It's too far to cover on foot alone. Time to stringify and glide over there.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804001_TextContext_Role128: Is this the Comos internal defense system? Feels... dangerous.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801003_TextContext_Role128: The city's already started to undergo reverstring, and the Big Collapse is close.
SequenceDialogue.Row9804010_TextContext_Role133: The path ahead is blocked. There's no choice - I'll have to wall-stick my way through.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801045_TextContext_Role124: Stay true to your resolve until the day we conquer the collapse syndrome.
SequenceDialogue.Row9801043_TextContext_Role124: It will surely be a long journey
SequenceDialogue.Row9804037_TextContext_Role131: Enemy incursion detected at A3. Requesting support!

SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9611104_TextContext_Player: "That's why we fight to protect everything."
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604054_TextContext_Role146: Mother often says, "At least classical art seems safe!"
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501033_TextContext_Role105: ...I didn't expect it to be this simple. This kind of communication skill isn't in my negotiation manual.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146116_TextContext_Role146: All my life, I've had this dream. A world where everyone has a place to call home, regardless of their wealth, their age, or their status. You’ll be with me to make it happen, right?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605034_TextContext_Player: You keep yawning. Are you not sleeping well, Celestia?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605019_TextContext_Role146: Three days?! How could this... In my mind, it's only been a single day!!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605039_TextContext_Player: Stop trying to be strong. Sit down!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605014_TextContext_Player: It's not! We haven't seen each other at all in the last few days!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604012_TextContext_Player: Nope, I'm ok, just almost fried my brain with some wild fantasies!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601018_TextContext_Role146: Stop right there! You must to take care of yourself!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603021_TextContext_Player: Just don't hold on too tightly. You might burn yourself!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604017_TextContext_Player: Great instinct, keep thinking that way!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101025_TextContext_Role101: To make sure I don't give up when things get tough, I must gather all the courage and determination I can!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101006_TextContext_Role101: To thank you for always looking out for me, I've got a little surprise for you... Think of it as our special memento!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105028_TextContext_Role105: Why do I seek your understanding when I'm tired? Perhaps I've come to rely on you. If just a little more.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604052_TextContext_Role146: I've been following it online for a long time, but I just couldn't decide. You really need to see it in person to feel the impact of modern art!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604007_TextContext_Role146: I was the best volleyball player on my team for three years running!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603003_TextContext_Role146: I said I wanted to gaze at the stars together, but now that you're finally here, there aren't any in sight.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601009_TextContext_Role998: There was an explosion nearby, and you were caught in the middle of it...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146118_TextContext_Role146: I don’t know why, but every time I’m around you, I get this tiny but incredible feeling deep inside my heart.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603007_TextContext_Role146: So, the forecast isn't always accurate. Sometimes, there are even unexpected surprises.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146111_TextContext_Role146: I made a bunch of origami stars. If people could truly find happiness through my prayers, that would be amazing.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105205_TextContext_Role105: That's it for today's music sharing. We'll listen to your playlist next time.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601021_TextContext_Player: The feeling of those devices moving around my body is so weird...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603012_TextContext_Role146: Someone's got a high opinion of themselves!!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146068_TextContext_Role146: Your happiness means the world to me I finally understand the light that I've been searching for has been you all this time, Navigator.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601011_TextContext_Role998: Just to be safe, I took you back to my clinic to get some rest.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603013_TextContext_Role146: ...I'm not sure why, but your words are like starlight piercing through the clouds, lighting me up...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602011_TextContext_Role146: But I'm not as confident it will suit anyone else's taste.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101011_TextContext_Role101: But hey, that's me—on a mission to be a super cool, gamer-style investigator!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820028_TextContext_Role146: I've got a gift for you, as a show of thanks.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501018_TextContext_Role105: Y-You could be a friend of the Groves...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146205_TextContext_Role146:
You’re interested in rescue missions too?
I know you have good intentions, but sorry, I need to handle these tasks on my own.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101205_TextContext_Role101: Hm? You want to play with it too, don't you? Well, go ahead!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501023_TextContext_Player: You didn't sound like a friend...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146055_TextContext_Role146: Seems like you've got mail. Perhaps it's something important? Don't wait, go now and check it out quickly.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105002_TextContext_Role105:
Are you really... that strong?
(Cough) What I meant was that I wanted to recognize your abilities.
Is my praise not worthy of your happiness?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146067_TextContext_Role146: You look worn out. Come rest with me for a while. I can assist you in refining the battle plan.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105022_TextContext_Role105:
Hard to believe the Grove family experienced such internal strife, isn't it?
But as one who has lived through it, I'm acutely aware of the twists and turns of our family history.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105023_TextContext_Role105:
Want to partner up?
You'll find that I have exacting standards for those who work with me.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501012_TextContext_Player: You want me as your business partner?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146114_TextContext_Role146: Oh? Are you trying to praise me? Thank you
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602001_TextContext_Role146: You're here! Just give me a moment. Things are a bit messy...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146203_TextContext_Role146: Oh? …You’re here? Please wait a moment I'm checking on the recent rescue missions.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501016_TextContext_Role105: I find your attitude... somewhat unexpected. The Grove family is reputable and respected in both the business and finance sectors. I don't see a single reason why you would say no.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105103_TextContext_Role105:
Would you like a cup of black tea? I brewed it myself.
Of course, if you'd rather not drink, that's fine with me. Hmph!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602009_TextContext_Role146: Why don't you give it a try? This is my first attempt at making jam.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604041_TextContext_Role146: Honestly, I don't know that much about Meredith, so I was hoping you could give me some ideas.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602034_TextContext_Role146: Actually, I made a few other flavors too...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601030_TextContext_Player: I feel like something inside me has fallen apart...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601024_TextContext_Role146: Just hold on a little longer. I'll be done in no time.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101002_TextContext_Role101: Let me introduce myself again. I'm Michele, and I love cats and gaming...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501030_TextContext_Role105: I would like to reiterate that the friendship I desire is one that's long-lasting and stable. You will be my most valuable ally. Your wishes and demands will also be respected to the greatest extent possible as reflected in the contract.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603023_TextContext_Role146: I won't be able to keep a straight face if you keep this up.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146058_TextContext_Role146: Just now, I discovered a new purpose—to become your strength. If I can be of any help, please, count on me from now on.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146207_TextContext_Role146: Even in this so-called utopian world of Strinova, there are countless people oppressed by poverty. I must do what I can for them, no matter how small.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101010_TextContext_Role101: Wow... You really know me! Honestly, I never imagined I’d receive a gift this special. Thank you so much...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101020_TextContext_Role101: I was a tad worried that you might not be into video games...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604022_TextContext_Role146: A mere thank you doesn’t quite cut it, so I wanted to prepare a gift for everyone!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101020_TextContext_Role101: Maybe I'll get to fully enjoy my games once the battles are over.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101204_TextContext_Role101: Whenever I'm around, my kitty seems to get extra playful!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146054_TextContext_Role146: As long as we all work together, no enemy will be daunting. Keep pushing forward!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501017_TextContext_Role105: Darn it. I have never failed a business negotiation... Are you sure you don't want to reconsider? I'm hoping that...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605036_TextContext_Role146: Regret, guilt, self-criticism… I end up losing track of time, so I haven’t been sleeping much…
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101003_TextContext_Role101: Just like that. All your worries are gone.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605024_TextContext_Role146: Wha! How did this happen?! Such laziness, such carelessness...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9603001_TextContext_Role146: Phew... So, this is what a consciousness link feels like.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605013_TextContext_Role146: Hehe. It must be. We only saw each other yesterday!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101006_TextContext_Role101: You don't know, do you? I guess it’s true what they say, looks can be deceiving.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603020_TextContext_Player: Take as much as you want. There's plenty more where it came from!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105024_TextContext_Role105: Hmpf! This is just typical for you, isn't it? Being rude like that!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101013_TextContext_Role101:
Mmm... Did you write something on my hand?
Is this some kind of game?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604006_TextContext_Role146: Waah. It's a pity that I'm busy with the Astral Sanctuary. I would have liked to give it a try...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605046_TextContext_Role146: Mmm... It's a bit noisy... but very comforting...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605038_TextContext_Role146: Ugh, I stood up too fast… feeling a bit lightheaded…
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605008_TextContext_Role146: Ehm. Forget it... You've already seen me like this anyway...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605029_TextContext_Role146: Ah, well... The important thing is to get in contact with everyone and head to the Astral Sanctuary. A lot of work must have piled up in my absence!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501019_TextContext_Player: Business cooperation is not in my area of expertise.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820006_TextContext_Role146: Ah! I forgot to introduce myself.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601008_TextContext_Role146: Ah... Maybe I said too much...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601015_TextContext_Role146: Hmm—You haven't really given it much thought until now, am I right?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605035_TextContext_Role146: Um... When I'm alone, my mind tends to wander to all kinds of complicated feelings...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101005_TextContext_Role101: Hmm... We’ve just got a new email! Let’s have a look what’s inside!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604044_TextContext_Role146: Ah. So that's the kind of stuff that Meredith likes. I've got it!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601026_TextContext_Role146: Perfect, you're holding up well. I'm done now.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603036_TextContext_Role146: Mhmm! Today turned out to be unexpectedly perfect.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9602003_TextContext_Role146: Mhm. I'm sure you'll ace the inspection.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146112_TextContext_Role146:
Oh? Do you need something from me?
If you ever need my help, please don’t hesitate to ask.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101004_TextContext_Role101: Hehe, you'd never guess, but that person is actually...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605020_TextContext_Role146: I wanted to think more about the Astral Sanctuary and my mother, so I tried to create a quiet environment for myself...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602024_TextContext_Role146: It's just that I put a lot into making this jam, so I'm eager for some feedback.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601014_TextContext_Role146: That's why most people sign up for a check-up after they've been in Strinova for a while.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820014_TextContext_Role146: In my view, Navigators deserve a lot of respect.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601018_TextContext_Role146: To me, you're more like my senior and my colleague.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601002_TextContext_Aside: In the midst of our sky-bound journey,
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501011_TextContext_Role105: Based on our previous cooperation, I am interested in establishing a long-term partnership with you. Together, we will be unstoppable!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604021_TextContext_Role146: Thanks to everyone's help, the Astral Sanctuary isn't in danger anymore.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105009_TextContext_Role105:
It's all thanks to you.
Don't give me that look. I know when to thank you, and I'll say it clearly!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603039_TextContext_Role146: It's probably because of a “certain someone!”
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501007_TextContext_Role105: With the election fast approaching, the Grove family shall become the leader of the business world for the next decade.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603034_TextContext_Player: The forecast was a total mess!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604057_TextContext_Role146: That's great! Next time... let's go to an art exhibition together!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601007_TextContext_Role998: Thank goodness! You're finally awake, I was so worried!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602033_TextContext_Role146: That's great! That's a load off my mind~
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602025_TextContext_Role146: But if I'm too anxious, I'll end up putting pressure on you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820016_TextContext_Role146: To lose one's memory is to lose one's self. Only by relying on Navigators like you can people find themselves once more.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101022_TextContext_Role101: It's been ages since I've gamed with someone at home. What do you think? A story of adventures shared by an investigator and a navigator sounds pretty exciting, right?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605027_TextContext_Player: Okay! I've updated everyone on your situation.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605026_TextContext_Player: Alright. I've sent your message to the group chat.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105021_TextContext_Role105:
I'd describe us as traveling companions now, but I'd much rather wish we were more!
Only feelings that have survived the crucible of adversity can stand the test of time.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820019_TextContext_Role146: If the day comes when I'm “reincarnated,” please make sure to transfer my memory back and help guide me... so that I can become Astierred once more.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501006_TextContext_Role105: If one were to compare the entire business world to a giant cruise ship, the leader would be the person steering the ship and determining its course.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146120_TextContext_Role146: If we can gift these stars to the people at Astral Sanctuary, their lives might be filled with a bit more hope. That would make you happy too, right?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105020_TextContext_Role105:
My family's legacy teaches that we must look toward the future.
Only then, can we endure.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105012_TextContext_Role105:
By the way, there's something I forgot to tell you.
You have no right to look into my history without my express permission!
In any case, I know nothing about what will happen...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605032_TextContext_Role146: That's right! We've gotta recharge the communicator right away!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101011_TextContext_Role101: I'm really curious about you! Don't you have any secrets you want to share with me?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101024_TextContext_Role101:
Even if the Scissors have their reasons to rebel, using such extreme methods is just not right.
Anyways, I just don’t get them.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9604004_TextContext_Role146: Even someone like me... has a reason to fight.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601009_TextContext_Role146: I almost forgot about the task at hand!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9604007_TextContext_Role146: I hope your kindness can protect everyone, Navigator.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601017_TextContext_Role146: Your role is to help stabilize our mental states, and to prevent the onset of Collapse Syndrome.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604003_TextContext_Role146: Strian's always like this. It is a famous resort, after all!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604013_TextContext_Role146: Fantasies...? It's times like these where I don't have a clue what's going through your mind.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601019_TextContext_Role146: The Navigator is a great doctor whom everyone respects.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101001_TextContext_Role101: Navigator, you made it! Welcome, welcome!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501010_TextContext_Role105: Become a friend of the Grove family, Navigator!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101012_TextContext_Role101: Hey, Navigator! We've got some rare free time. Fancy a challenge between gamers?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601013_TextContext_Role146: Though adverse reactions to stringification are rare, they're still a concern.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605011_TextContext_Player: I wanted to see you, obviously!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604004_TextContext_Role146: Of course, the main reason is the beach volleyball competition held by the bay. It's been going on all week.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602006_TextContext_Role146: Of course, there's some for you too. That's why I invited you over!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820029_TextContext_Role146: From now on, my memory is in your hands.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604055_TextContext_Role146: I'm so glad you're willing to appreciate this kind of stuff with me...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604032_TextContext_Role146: As for Kokona... Oh? I didn't expect to find this here!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601032_TextContext_Role146: Maybe you're just feeling down because you're hungry...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105005_TextContext_Role105:
Don't forget to check your mail.
If it were anyone other than you, I would not take such great pains to remind you of this!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105003_TextContext_Role105:
Ehm... I'm not good at comforting others... Hey you, how do you want to console yourself?
Would you prefer a pat on the shoulder or your head?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105206_TextContext_Role105:
What? Do you not understand what I'm saying?
Come and sing with me!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604014_TextContext_Role146: Then again, I also get the feeling that it's a blessing I don't know what you're thinking right now...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605012_TextContext_Role146: I feel as if we haven't seen each other in a while... Am I overthinking it?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820008_TextContext_Role146: As I'm sure you know, Urbino provides funding to members who run public welfare organizations.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601012_TextContext_Role146: You're still a newcomer to Strinova, right?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601027_TextContext_Role146: Your in excellent shape, no issues at all!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601021_TextContext_Role146: You'll need to use a memory chip to synchronize with me and record all my actions.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146406_TextContext_Role146:
Want to fold origami stars with me?
But before that, let's take a moment to think about all the wishes we should make.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105203_TextContext_Role105:
Wha?! I wasn't secretly listening to rock!
I can't believe you would suddenly show up out-of-the-blue without saying something first...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605047_TextContext_Role146: I... I'll rest... for a while...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146108_TextContext_Role146: I won’t hide anything from you. But, why did you ask about that? This subtle sensation in my heart, what is it even supposed to mean?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101012_TextContext_Role101: I'm not a kid anymore! Hehehe!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101026_TextContext_Role101: I never see naivety as a flaw; those seemingly unrealistic dreams might just hide the life everyone truly desires…
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146059_TextContext_Role146: It's been forever since we last met, hasn't it? Each day without you felt like forever. These days were so empty for me... Please, can you promise not to be away for so long next time? I truly hope you can stay by my side.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601014_TextContext_Role146: We arranged a Mindlock Inspection today to check and record my conditions.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820022_TextContext_Player: I'll perform my duties as a Navigator.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105106_TextContext_Role105: I didn't come here on purpose. I'm just curious about what you've been working on.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605005_TextContext_Role146: I'm home... You're being too loud. The neighbors are going to complain...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820010_TextContext_Role146: I was one of the first on the scene after receiving the rescue mission from Area 88 and found you lying on the pavement.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105027_TextContext_Role105:
I don't deny the possibility of betrayal still exists, but if it were to be you, perhaps I could accept that...
Hmpf! You don't seem like you'd dare betray my trust anyway!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105011_TextContext_Role105: The only reason I'm still here is to keep a better eye on that which concerns me. It wasn't all for you!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604053_TextContext_Role146: I'm a huge fan of modern art, but mother likes the classics much more.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101028_TextContext_Role101:
I always feel like I'm destined for something special... like curing the Collapse Syndrome or taking down The Scissors.
Huh? I'm not kidding, I mean it!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604039_TextContext_Player: I'm sure that Kokona will be able to feel your sincerity...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501013_TextContext_Role105: The relationship I would like to establish is more than just business...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105001_TextContext_Role105:
This type of victory doesn't satisfy you, am I right?
Why don't we go for another?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501020_TextContext_Role105: That's... That's not what I meant! I said, “friend.”
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601007_TextContext_Role146: My home in Star Street is only a few blocks away from the bay. If you'd like, I could show you the beautiful coastal scenery.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605016_TextContext_Role146: I’ve only been home for a day, right?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501004_TextContext_Role105: I'm going to tell you something you're probably already aware of.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603005_TextContext_Player: I read the forecast carefully. There should have been stars out tonight.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820007_TextContext_Role146: I'm Celestia. I work as a medic for Urbino. This is my room in the Astral Sanctuary.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501002_TextContext_Role105: Audrey Grove, current head of the Grove Corporation. A pleasure to meet you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501014_TextContext_Player: I'm a navigator, not a businessperson...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105026_TextContext_Role105:
When I lost my memory, everything around me felt alien.
But this experience taught me that what matters most isn't glory, fame, or fortune but rather the true purity of feeling.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820011_TextContext_Role146: I took a look at your ID, and it turned out you were my Navigator. Such coincidence.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101001_TextContext_Role101: Yay! I knew it, you really did win!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603015_TextContext_Player: My light and warmth - I've got plenty to spare for Celestia!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501028_TextContext_Role105: I was quite sincere with you!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101023_TextContext_Role101: I believe that as long as we maintain order in Strinova, everyone can live happy lives.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101022_TextContext_Role101:
What does true justice mean to me?
That’s definitely going to need some serious thought.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146109_TextContext_Role146: I really do care about this world. However so many things make me feel anxious and uneasy I know that what I do may not change much but I can't stop pushing forward.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105004_TextContext_Role105: I understand you must be very unhappy about it... That's why, in the next battle, you're gonna have to get them back with me!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146115_TextContext_Role146: Oh? I’ve waited a long time for you. Thank you for being here.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602010_TextContext_Role146: It tasted pretty good to me.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602031_TextContext_Player: I think it's definitely a taste that everyone should try!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146117_TextContext_Role146: Despite all my efforts, my mother doesn’t acknowledge them. Perhaps she thinks I should pursue the same path she did. Do you think it’s my fault?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820023_TextContext_Player: I still don't really get what it means to be a Navigator...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101103_TextContext_Role101: The latest anime ep is about to air. I've gotta eat quickly so I can catch it later~
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602005_TextContext_Role146: So, I decided to make some jam to share with everyone.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501009_TextContext_Player: What does all this have to do with me?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820018_TextContext_Role146: That's why I took the liberty of tracking you down. I need you to help capture my memories.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604051_TextContext_Role146: Thanks to you, I've picked out some great gifts!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105006_TextContext_Role105:
Take it. It's a gift.
Doing nothing would hardly be an act of gratitude...
In any case, I just felt like giving you a little praise.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105105_TextContext_Role105: They say similarity in your taste in tea indicates similarity in many other areas as well.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9604006_TextContext_Role146: From now on, you may encounter more people and challenges.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820025_TextContext_Role146: Alright. I'm off to the Departure Zone. There's a PUS rescue mission that I'm needed for.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820030_TextContext_Role146: Now, then, you're free to explore Strinova.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9602005_TextContext_Aside: Approaching Anchor Point: Departure Zone - P.U.S. Rescue Mission.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146107_TextContext_Role146: Don’t worry, I usually don't carry any weapons. Is there something you're worried about?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605017_TextContext_Player: It's been three days since you've left your home!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601006_TextContext_Role146: Isn't the environment in Strian just wonderful? Green trees, the seaside, and idyllic farms. It's the perfect place to relax.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603006_TextContext_Role146: Strian mimics Earth’s natural rules for realistic simulation.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604048_TextContext_Role146: It ticks the “dog” and “pyramid” boxes, and the design is quite edgy!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105010_TextContext_Role105: Since you've expressed your admiration with such sincerity, allow me to accept your present. After all, that is not impermissible... Hmph. Stop overthinking it!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603024_TextContext_Role146: Tonight's atmosphere was supposed to be solemn. But, you being here with me...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105025_TextContext_Role105: Do you understand? I'm not one for changing my mind easily.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820009_TextContext_Role146: That's what the Astral Sanctuary does. We provide treatment to Strinovians in need.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604008_TextContext_Player: Celestia... beach... volleyball... what an unbeatable combo~
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604023_TextContext_Player: Aren't you super broke right now?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602003_TextContext_Role146: I helped treat some of the workers at the Eco Park. I guess this was their way of paying me back.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604035_TextContext_Role146: It's a model from an old Urbino multi-dimensional art collection!!!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604038_TextContext_Player: This one's definitely gonna leave her speechless. Not a bad choice!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603032_TextContext_Role146: It's a shooting star! It's gotta be!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820013_TextContext_Role146: That's right. It was your first day... you must not be used to the title yet.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601016_TextContext_Role146: That's right. Carrying out daily scheduled inspections is part of your job as a Navigator.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605018_TextContext_Player: You're so confused! Two days have already passed!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602023_TextContext_Role146: Oooh... Sorry. I shouldn't be rushing you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603019_TextContext_Role146: Such a comforting light, I can feel its warmth in my hands...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146401_TextContext_Role146:
Good evening, have you ever had ice cream at night? It's really something special.
There's one cup left. Want to enjoy it together?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101106_TextContext_Role101: There's a comic con happening in Arton City right now. If you're free, would you like to come with me? I've got a ton of merch I want to buy!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603026_TextContext_Player: With unexpected surprises come unexpected fortunes~
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101021_TextContext_Role101: Need help? Just call for the investigator! I’m always ready for action.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603010_TextContext_Player: With a shining star like me, do you really need any others?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101013_TextContext_Role101: You can choose between Paper Detective, a contender for Best Story of the Year, or Superheroes of Justice, a classic action game filled with childhood nostalgia. Which adventure are you up for?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501021_TextContext_Role105: Is this concept so difficult to understand... I would like you to be my navigator; for us to establish...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101014_TextContext_Role101:
Let's make a promise!
No matter what becomes of this world, we’ll always be together.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105204_TextContext_Role105: It doesn't hurt to listen to other genres once a in while.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105014_TextContext_Role105:
The Grove family doesn't need a haughty mistress. It needs a wise and proper leader.
I still don't know whether the person I am today is a proper reflection of all the hopes invested in me.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604026_TextContext_Role146: Meredith and Kokona... I wonder what they would like?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101203_TextContext_Role101:
Welcome home! Wait, that's not right... Welcome to my place!
Hehe, isn't it cute!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605042_TextContext_Role146: Huh, I... I just sat down without thinking...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604010_TextContext_Role146: Hm? You've got a strange expression on your face. Is the heat getting to you?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601029_TextContext_Role146: Hmm, why do you look so down?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605015_TextContext_Role146: Eh? What?! Didn't... didn't we just hang out yesterday...?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146404_TextContext_Role146: Huh? You brought dessert for me?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604018_TextContext_Role146: Eh?! My instincts are telling me not to dig any deeper...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101027_TextContext_Role101:
Justice is a creed. The ideal investigator should have the resolve to save the world!
But... when will I finally become that person?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601004_TextContext_Player: I guess this counts as an excuse to stretch one's legs.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101016_TextContext_Role101: And guess what? They gave it to us for free. Let's dive in and see what it feels like to be a "Great Detective"!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101009_TextContext_Role101: Receiving a gift from you always makes me happy!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501005_TextContext_Role105: Urbino leader elections take place once a decade. This is a significant event in all of Urbino.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604056_TextContext_Player: I'm a super open-minded person, after all!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605043_TextContext_Role146: The sofa and pillows... so soft... such a familiar scent...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604016_TextContext_Player: It’s fine, I wouldn’t want to be seen as a weirdo anyway~
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605037_TextContext_Role146: Don't worry. I feel fine. I can get to work...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604025_TextContext_Role146: But that's fine! I'll get through it! These gifts are more important right now!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820002_TextContext_Role146: An explosion on my first day...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604009_TextContext_Player: I didn't think that Celestia would be so into sports!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601016_TextContext_Player: Nope, things have been super busy lately~
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604049_TextContext_Player: It's fine. Meredith's not the kind to complain anyway...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603037_TextContext_Role146: A shooting star signifies good fortune, so things should go smoothly from now on~
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605048_TextContext_Role146: And then... then... back to work... work...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605021_TextContext_Role146: After that, I got lost in my thoughts and completely lost track of the outside world...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101010_TextContext_Role101: An investigator by day, a gamer by night. Does that sound a bit odd to you?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603009_TextContext_Player: Look! Aren't there two stars right here?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501031_TextContext_Role105: Now, would you consider... being my friend?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601031_TextContext_Player: I'm no longer the person I once was...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604028_TextContext_Role146: Mr. Bai already told me he wants me to convert all my thanks into money.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604024_TextContext_Role146: Yeah. I'm afraid that for the near future, I'll probably have to survive on just instant noodles...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601010_TextContext_Role998: You passed out, but I quickly checked you over and found no visible injuries.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146119_TextContext_Role146: Notice that light over there? It's coming from the indoor planetarium. With its help, we can enjoy the stars regardless of the weather.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603025_TextContext_Role146: It's incredible. It's like you've completely turned everything on its head...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604050_TextContext_Player: Such a unique style. I feel like I've seen another side to Celestia today...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820003_TextContext_Role146: It must be rough for you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602029_TextContext_Role146: You're really taking this seriously. I've only seen food critics be this meticulous
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601017_TextContext_Player: What, that's a thing?! I've been stuck on the battlefield most of the time...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820027_TextContext_Role146: This is the first time our consciousnesses have connected... Thank you very much for your cooperation!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605022_TextContext_Role146: Wait a second, I had my communicator on. Where did it go...?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601011_TextContext_Role146: It's nothing too serious, so please don't worry~
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101019_TextContext_Role101: It's time to find out how well we work together as a team. Show me what you've got, Navigator!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604029_TextContext_Role146: And... he even provided me the exchange rate in advance, the 'gratitude-to-cash' rate...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501008_TextContext_Role105: And I happen to be the most promising candidate in the upcoming election!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602035_TextContext_Role146: Maybe you can help me taste those, too?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501034_TextContext_Role105: You're truly a worthy ally of mine, having easily accomplished such a feat. I must not underestimate you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820015_TextContext_Role146: Ever since the outbreak of collapse syndrome, the people of Strinova go through a memory reset once every hundred years.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105104_TextContext_Role105: Petals and candied fruit combined with the richness of the black tea. Truly a perfect blend.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602004_TextContext_Role146: I appreciate the gift. It's just... figuring out what to do with all these apples has been quite a headache.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603033_TextContext_Role146: I only saw the tail end, but it couldn't be anything else!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604015_TextContext_Role146: That might have been a little rude...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15105013_TextContext_Role105:
If you think this brings us closer together, you're very badly mistaken!
But... If you show enough sincerity, perhaps I can give you some consideration...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820021_TextContext_Role146: Everything you record will be stored inside, so keep it safe.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101003_TextContext_Role101: Speaking of games, if you regularly visit 'The No.1 Gaming Forum,' you must have heard of the famous moderator 'Super Meow Guardian,' who posts game guides and news...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820024_TextContext_Role146: Oh right! Given that it's your first day, you've probably never done this before.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101105_TextContext_Role101: Huh? You came to hang out with me again? I was just about to watch another episode... but hanging out with you sounds good too.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101002_TextContext_Role101: Huh? If you ask me who's the best right now? It's obviously you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602026_TextContext_Role146: Don't mind me! Take your time and enjoy it!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820020_TextContext_Role146: Please use your memory chip to record those memories tied to me.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601023_TextContext_Role146: Please relax. Being anxious isn't going to help the examination go by any faster. Stop being such a child.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820026_TextContext_Role146: This will be a good opportunity to record the mission and get familiar with your work.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501001_TextContext_Role105: Excuse me, are you the Navigator? We worked together during the Grove Bank Incident. Do you remember?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501024_TextContext_Role105: Isn't that how cooperation is supposed to be?!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146056_TextContext_Role146: Thanks for sticking with me. I've got a gift for you that I've been preparing for a long time. Please... please accept it.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146057_TextContext_Role146: Thank you for accompanying me all this time.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9604002_TextContext_Player: Do you also need to work in the field?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9604001_TextContext_Player: Thank you for your hard work.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15101004_TextContext_Role101: Hey! Listen to me, I don't care about winning or losing! To me, you're already the best.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9820017_TextContext_Role146: For reasons unknown, the “The Second Collapse” occurred much earlier than the previous one. I'm worried that my reverse-stringification has been accelerated, too.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604019_TextContext_Role146: Let's get back to the topic at hand - presents!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601013_TextContext_Role998: Oh! I forgot to introduce myself. I'm Celestia, the one in charge of this Astral Sanctuary.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605040_TextContext_Player: This calls for some strictness—sit down!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101018_TextContext_Role101: This was a big hit back on Old Earth, a co-op RPG that's all about teamwork.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101008_TextContext_Role101: How did you figure it out so quickly? You really do have a sharp eye!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146066_TextContext_Role146: This was actually my responsibility, so please, please don't feel so down.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604005_TextContext_Role146: It's a tradition around these parts. The winning team gets to eat for free at Strian's most exclusive restaurant for an entire year!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146052_TextContext_Role146: This was a real team effort.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604031_TextContext_Player: Is he the incarnation of some strange creature? The kind that swallows gold...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9603003_TextContext_Role146: I picked up this gift for you yesterday. Please, accept my gratitude!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601028_TextContext_Role146: It's rare to find someone in such good shape. Don't slack off now!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146065_TextContext_Role146: It's because of everyone's efforts that we achieved this. So, thank you for your help. I hope I can always stay by your side.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146305_TextContext_Role146:
Being this close, I can see your face so clearly.
If it’s okay with you... could we hold onto this moment a little longer?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146307_TextContext_Role146:
Being this close, I can see your face so clearly.
If it’s okay with you... could we hold onto this moment a little longer?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101015_TextContext_Role101: This one's based on the hit TV series, a text adventure with twists and turns that'll keep you hooked. Even our chief investigators are recommending it.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10501029_TextContext_Role105: Here is a contract. I hope you don't mind. It's a family tradition; we have always valued contracts and commitments.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604037_TextContext_Role146: Kokona's gift has been decided! What do you think?!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605009_TextContext_Role146: So... Why did you come here...?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604040_TextContext_Role146: Kokona's decided, then. Now, for Meredith...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101009_TextContext_Role101: Hmm, let's get to know each other a bit better, shall we? I work as an investigator, but off the clock, I'm just Michele, the gamer. My ID is Super Pawtector.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row10101021_TextContext_Role101: But now that you're onboard, you're officially my gaming partner! Here's your controller; take a moment to get a feel for the joystick and the quick buttons.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602013_TextContext_Player: I'll be the first to brave this frontier of flavor!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row9601020_TextContext_Player: So... how should we go about this?
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604036_TextContext_Role146: They only put out a limited release of a thousand models, and they all sold out within minutes of launch. To be able to find one of them at such a small store... today's my lucky day!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146103_TextContext_Role146: Ready for action anytime. Just give me the word, and I'll be good to go.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row15146208_TextContext_Role146: Ready for action anytime. Just give me the word, and I'll be good to go.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601033_TextContext_Role146: Since you're here in Strian, let me treat you to a local delicacy - bonsai cake!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605002_TextContext_Aside: (She hasn't left her dorm in several days!)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601034_TextContext_Aside: (Afterward, Celestia treated me to a delicious bonsai cake, but I still feel differently than I did before...)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602018_TextContext_Aside: (The hellishly sweet taste rushed down my throat and coated my every sense, sending shivers down my spine.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604034_TextContext_Aside: (Its tendrils, each covered with myriad eyes, twist into a ball-shaped object. Only the three pairs of wings on the back bear any resemblance to an angel...)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605049_TextContext_Role146: (Quietly) Thank you... for checking on me.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605023_TextContext_Player: (Pointing) Under the table, it's out of power.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604002_TextContext_Player: (Feeling boxed in) This really is a tourist trap. Look at how many people showed up!
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605001_TextContext_Aside: (Star Street, Strian, the door to Celestia's dorm... what am I doing here...?)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603001_TextContext_Aside: Strian, the bay below the Eco-Park. The cold wind blows against the rushing waves, creating a loud symphony.
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603031_TextContext_Aside: (In the empty night sky, a bright star suddenly began streaking across the expanse before quickly disappearing under the sea.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604033_TextContext_Aside: (Celestia held up a small wooden sculpture with the word "Angel" engraved on its base... Eh? Is this thing really an angel?!)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14602015_TextContext_Aside: (As Celestia carefully takes out the jam and twisted off the lid, a sweet aroma wafts out. This scent...?)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604046_TextContext_Aside: (Celestia held up what appeared to be a... sewn fabric dog? At least it looks like a dog. Probably.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14601020_TextContext_Aside: (Her face growing serious, Celestia pushed me down onto the chair and started attaching strange devices to my body.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14603017_TextContext_Aside: (All of a sudden, Celestia stretched out her hands in my direction, with care, as if she were picking up something from the void.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14605045_TextContext_Player: (Whispering) Go to sleep... go to sleep... go to sleep...
SequenceDialogueApartment.Row14604047_TextContext_Aside: (Its big head made out of black cloth is completely disproportionate to its small body. There's a pyramid on its head for some reason. One of its eyes is way smaller than the other. Its tooth seems to be made out of some kind of bone polished to look like a real dog's tooth. Why go to such lengths for this level of detail in something so bizarre...?)

SequenceMap.97003_Desc: Area 88 was one of the first areas established in Neutroville. It's home to some of the world's oldest buildings and still serves as a busy traffic artery and commercial hub today.
SequenceMap.97002_Desc: Bablo Crystals consist of two components: the crystal body itself and the virtual matter inside. The virtual matter is of no use to Strinovians, meaning that crystals need to be purified before use.
SequenceMap.97013_Desc: The Komos Tower defense system exists in a virtual space that imitates the environment of the True Wilderness. Intruders are subject to an overwhelming sense of discomfort and disorder, before eventually succumbing to the fate of reverstringification.
SequenceMap.97001_Desc: Komos Tower serves as the energy hub for each city. The String Energy generated by the resonance of abundant Bablo Crystals maintains regional stability, suppressing the occurrences of [Collapse Syndrome] and [Reverstringification].

Skill.1335_AwakenSketch: Active skills ricochet and generate an additional field
Skill.1244_AwakenSketch: Active skills heal a large amount of HP

ST_Career.RankInfoPageDesc2:
<Rank-Title>1.</> Strinovium points increase or decrease based on performance and match outcome.
<Rank-Title>2.</> Reach 100 Strinovium points to rank up (some players may skip sub-ranks for their performance). Losing at 0 points results in rank demotion.
ST_Career.RankInfoPageDesc3:
<Rank-Title>1.</> When you reach Superstring rank and your Strinovium Points are 0, one loss triggers rank protection. A second loss will demote you to Quark I.
<Rank-Title>2.</> If you don't play a Ranked match for <Rank-Red>7 consecutive days</>, you'll lose 30 Superstring Points, down to a minimum of 0.
<Rank-Title>3.</> At 200 Superstring Points, ranking in the top 500 promotes you to Singularity rank, while falling below the top 500 drops you back to Superstring rank.
<Rank-Title>4.</> Superstring and Singularity ranks are limited to solo or duo queues only.
ST_Career.RankInfoPageDesc1:
<Rank-Title>Participation Rules:</> Reach <Rank-Red>Lv. 10</> to unlock ranked matches.
<Rank-Title>Season Duration:</> Each season lasts around 2 months. At the end of a season, rewards are given based on the highest rank achieved. A new season begins with placement matches to determine your initial rank.
<Rank-Title>Rank Structure:</> There are 9 major ranks, which are further divided into several sub-ranks.
ST_Career.LeisureRuleText3: As with ranked matches, each season lasts around 2 months. When a season ends, you'll receive rewards based on your highest rank during that season. Your rank will reset at the beginning of the next season.

ST_Career.LeisureRuleText2: Earn challenge points by participating in any match mode. Challenge points can only increase (you won't lose any on defeats). When you reach the highest rank of Monarch, you'll still be able to earn points and star up.
ST_Career.LeisureRuleText1: You can select and enter matchmaking for multiple modes at the same time. A battle will begin when there are sufficient players for any mode present in the queue.

ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Kill_1:
<Black_Bold_24>Double Kill Count:</>
Number of times you defeat 2 enemies in a row within 5 minutes.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Kill_2:
<Black_Bold_24>Triple Kill Count:</>
Number of times you defeat 3 enemies in a row within 5 minutes.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Kill_3:
<Black_Bold_24>Quadruple Kill Count:</>
Number of times you defeat 4 enemies in a row within 5 minutes.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Kill_4:
<Black_Bold_24>Penta Kill Count:</>
Number of times you defeat 5 enemies in a row within 5 minutes.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Cart_5:
<Black_Bold_24>Max Kill Streak:</>  
Highest number of kills in a single life.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Cart_3:
<Black_Bold_24>Conquest Damage:</>
Damage dealt to enemies within the payload control area, showcasing zone control.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Cart_4:
<Black_Bold_24>Conquest Counterattack Damage:</>
Damage dealt to enemies outside the payload area from within, reflecting defensive counterattack ability.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Body_3:
<Black_Bold_24>Survival Rate:</>
Percentage of battles survived after engaging in combat.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Shooting_5:
<Black_Bold_24>Damage Contribution:</>
Percentage of total damage you dealt when defeating or knocking down an enemy.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Shooting_3:
<Black_Bold_24>Defeat Time:</>
Time taken from attacking to defeating an enemy, shorter time means higher efficiency.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Blasting_1:
<Black_Bold_24>Round Plant Rate:</>
Percentage of rounds with successful bomb plants by your team as Attackers.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Shooting_4:
<Black_Bold_24>Reaction Time:</>
Time from spotting an enemy to taking action, measuring response speed.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Body_4:
<Black_Bold_24>Counter-Kill Rate:</>
Chance of successfully defeating an enemy after they attack first.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Shooting_2:
<Black_Bold_24>Accuracy:</>
Percentage of shots hitting the enemy, reflecting shooting stability.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Blasting_5:
<Black_Bold_24>Final Blow Rate:</>
Percentage of rounds won by your final kill.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Blasting_2:
<Black_Bold_24>First Hit Rate:</>
Percentage of rounds where you deal the first damage.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Blasting_3:
<Black_Bold_24>First Kill Rate:</>
Percentage of rounds where you are the first to damage or defeat an opponent, impacting early advantage.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Shooting_1:
<Black_Bold_24>Headshot Accuracy:</>
Percentage of shots hitting the enemy's head, higher indicates sharper aim.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Body_5:
<Black_Bold_24>Stringify Damage Reduction:</>
Total damage reduced while Stringifying.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Body_1:
<Black_Bold_24>Stringification Duration:</>
Total time spent actively using the Stringification ability in battles.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Body_2:
<Black_Bold_24>Stringify Evasion Rate:</>
Percentage of bullets successfully dodged while Stringifying.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Cart_1:
<Black_Bold_24>Escort Time:</>
Total time spent effectively moving the payload as an Attacker.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Blasting_4:
<Black_Bold_24>Clutch Win Rate:</>
Percentage of rounds won solo after all teammates are eliminated.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Kill_5:
<Black_Bold_24>Godlike Count:</>
Number of times you defeat more than 5 enemies in a row within 5 minutes.
ST_Common_LineTextPage.Radar_Cart_2:
<Black_Bold_24>Stop Time:</>
Total time spent effectively disrupting or blocking enemy attacks while defending the payload.

ST_CustomRoom.ReCommandDesc:
1. Room popularity is tied to the room code. To appear on the leaderboard, first generate and share the code.

2. Only the top 6 daily/weekly rule modes will be displayed on the leaderboard.

3. Daily leaderboards refresh at 6:00 AM the next day.

4. Weekly leaderboards refresh at 6:00 AM every Monday.

5. Popularity is determined by the number of participants and the duration of participation. Popularity increases faster with more participants and longer playtime.

ST_Friend.FriendBuffRule:
<FriendExplain_Black>Friends:</>
Max Friends: Your friend cap increases with your level.
<FriendExplain_Black>Friendship Interactions:</>
1. Play team matches (+7).
2. Give likes at the end of a match (+1).
3. Send private messages (+1 each).
<FriendExplain_Black>Friendship Details:</>
*You can earn up to 2 friendship points per day by interacting (likes/private messages) with each friend.
*You can get up to 150 points from friendship interactions and accepting friend requests each week.
*Limits refresh daily at 6:00 and weekly on Monday at 6:00.
*Friendship is one-directional and not shared by both players. Only playing on the same team will increase both players' friendship by the same amount. Other interactions only increase the friendship of the initiator.
<FriendExplain_Black>Friendship Levels:</>
Lv. 1: 0 points
Lv. 2: 50 points (basic relationship icon)
Lv. 3: 150 points (notification when friend comes online)
Lv. 4: 450 points (intermediate relationship icon)
Lv. 5: 900 points (advanced appearance sharing)
Lv. 6: 2100 points (advanced relationship icon)
Lv. 7: 3600 points (relationship display effect)
<FriendExplain_Black>Privileges:</>
1. Notification when friend comes online
When the friend comes online, a bubble notification will appear to let you quickly invite them to your team.
2. Appearance Sharing
Daily Charges: You'll be able to share appearances with your friend 2 times a day (only accepted shares are counted).
Advanced Appearances: When your friend has a Legendary appearance with advanced appearances unlocked, you'll be able to share appearances.
Glide Effect: When your friend has a glide effect with the corresponding appearance equipped, you'll be able to share glide effects.
Kill Effect: When your friend has a kill effect with the corresponding skin equipped, you'll be able to share kill effects.
3. Friendship Effects
Trigger Period: Effects can be triggered during the preparation phase before the start of a match.
Trigger Condition: Effects will automatically trigger when you're within 2m of your friend.
Activation Cooldown: Once an effect is triggered, it won't trigger again for 10s.
<FriendExplain_Black>System Settings:</>
You can disable SFX display through Settings.

[Skill Effect - Sol Battery] Each shot on an enemy accumulates Heat up to 100. At max Heat, DMG against stringified enemies increases. Other skills can consume Heat for boosts.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_133_P_1:
[Passive] Reduce <GrowthMB_DescY>gravity</> while hovering with Zeroth Rings.
[Skill Effect - Zeroth Rings] While airborne, Meredith's descent speed greatly reduces when aiming with weapons, skills, or tactical items.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_146_P_1:
[Passive] Increase Cosmic Recovery speed by <GrowthMB_DescY>{0}%</>.
[Skill Effect - Cosmic Recovery] Celestia gradually restores her own armor and that of nearby allies.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_128_P_1:
[Passive] Extend Shadow Reveal's enemy exposure time by <GrowthMB_DescY>{0}</>s.
[Skill Effect - Shadow Reveal] Enemies hit by Lawine's primary weapon are briefly exposed to her.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_205_P_1:
[Passive] Reduce Deception's decoy trigger cooldown by <GrowthMB_DescY>{0}</>s.
[Skill Effect - Deception] Galatea leaves behind a decoy whenever she unsticks from a wall. This passive only goes on cooldown if a decoy takes damage. Her decoys briefly detect nearby enemies not hidden behind obstacles, revealing them to her team. Enemies attacking the decoys are also temporarily exposed.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_205_P_2:
[Passive] Increase Deception's decoy duration by <GrowthMB_DescY>{0}</>s.
[Skill Effect - Deception] Galatea leaves behind a decoy whenever she unsticks from a wall. This passive only goes on cooldown if a decoy takes damage. Her decoys briefly detect nearby enemies not hidden behind obstacles, revealing them to her team. Enemies attacking the decoys are also temporarily exposed.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_121_P_1:
[Passive] Decrease <GrowthMB_DescY>DMG needed</> to trigger Toxin Burst.
[Skill Effect - Toxin Burst] Upon dealing sufficient HP damage to an enemy with her primary weapon, corrosive toxins erupt from the target, temporarily eroding the armor cap of nearby enemies.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_101_P_1:
[Passive] Kitty Tracer extends the exposure time of enemies by <GrowthMB_DescY>{0}</>s.
[Skill Effect - Kitty Tracer] Michele briefly reveals enemies when they hit her with direct weapon fire.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_105_P_1:
[Passive] Increase Royal Shield's ADS shield <GrowthMB_DescY>Max Value</>.
[Skill Effect - Royal Shield] Audrey generates a frontal shield when entering ADS or Deployment Mode, with increased shield capacity while deployed.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_105_P_2:
[Passive] Increase Royal Shield's shield recovery by <GrowthMB_DescY>{0}%</>.
[Skill Effect - Royal Shield] Audrey generates a frontal shield when entering ADS or Deployment Mode, with increased shield capacity while deployed.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_131_P_1:
[Passive] Increase Camouflage stealth entry speed by <GrowthMB_DescY>{0}%</>.
[Skill Effect - Camouflage] Yvette becomes camouflaged after standing still, remaining invisible to distant enemies and gradually visible to those closer.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_108_P_1:
[Passive] Extend Blinding Shot's weakening duration by <GrowthMB_DescY>{0}</>s.
[Skill Effect - Blinding Shot] Nobunaga charges his shots in ADS mode. Fully charged shots cause enemies to have increased shoulder-fire spread and lose their crosshairs with reduced accuracy while aiming down sight.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_107_P_1:
[Passive] Extend Paint Tracks' footprint exposure by <GrowthMB_DescY>{0}</>s.
[Skill Effect - Paint Tracks] Hits from Maddelena’s primary weapon slow enemies and expose their tracks.
ST_GrowthDefine.Details_109_P_1:
[Passive] Reduce Dawn's Insight activation time by <GrowthMB_DescY>{0}</>s.
[Skill Effect - Dawn's Insight] Reiichi periodically scans for enemies while in ADS mode. Scanned enemies are exposed briefly only to him.

ST_Login.PolicyTipsAge:
1. This is a casual online third-person tactical shooter, suitable for players aged 12 and older. Parental supervision is recommended for players under 18.
2. Set in a fantasy sci-fi world, this game is a work of fiction involving a series of main and side quests facilitated through conversations and interactions. Players assume the role of the Navigator, who guides the Strinovians in solving a global crisis and combating mysterious forces. The game features text-based and voice-based interaction systems, which comply with relevant laws and regulations.
3. Accounts will undergo real-name authentication. Verified minors will face the following restrictions:
- Gaming session time limits:
- Minors may only play the game from 8 pm to 9 pm on Fridays, Saturdays, Sundays, and public holidays.
- Payment restrictions for minors:
Players under the age of 12 may not make any purchases. Players aged 12-15 may spend up to CN¥50 in a single transaction, up to a monthly limit of CN¥200. Players aged 16-17 may spend up to CN¥100 in a single transaction, up to a monthly limit of CN¥400.
4. This game may be classified within the competitive arena shooting genre which may be of assistance in promoting player reaction speeds and hand-eye coordination. The scientific concepts, artwork, text, and actions within the game are designed to promote awareness of fundamental scientific concepts and their greater understanding.
