ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_200:
- Coordinate with your team to make use of the entire map.
- Don't give up control of the center.
- There are small entries that allow for alternate paths of action.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_112: Located in the bustling Port Euler, there's more to the warehouse with the designation "No.2 Depot" than meets the eye—According to intelligence, this is where crystals transported from the P.U.S Purification Center were randomly allocated...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_200: Built in the True Wilderness, Base 404 was secretly established by P.U.S for the development of the weapon "ZERO." This area is heavily fortified, and aside from its name, no other information has been disclosed.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_400: Built in the True Wilderness, Base 404 was secretly established by P.U.S for the development of the weapon "ZERO." This area is heavily fortified, and aside from its name, no other information has been disclosed.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_1003: Located on the outskirts of Neutroville, District 88 is a financial, commercial, and entertainment hub hailed by the citizens of Strinova as the "Wall Street of Utopia."
ST_MapCfg.Desc_1004: Located on the outskirts of Neutroville, District 88 is a financial, commercial, and entertainment hub hailed by the citizens of Strinova as the "Wall Street of Utopia."
ST_MapCfg.Desc_201: Located on the outskirts of Neutroville, District 88 is a financial, commercial, and entertainment hub hailed by the citizens of Strinova as the "Wall Street of Utopia."
ST_MapCfg.Desc_401: Located on the outskirts of Neutroville, District 88 is a financial, commercial, and entertainment hub hailed by the citizens of Strinova as the "Wall Street of Utopia."
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_202:
- Steer clear of the wastewater under the Central Generator District.
- Wall-stick to moving crates to find surprise angles on your enemies.
- Use the frag grenade on clumped-up enemies.
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_BombPass:
· Dealing damage can slow down enemies.

· Passing bombs can push players back.

· Items can be used to aid in escape.
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_207:
- Use trap doors to execute feint attacks.
- Avoid infrared traps to prevent triggering alarms.
- Obtain and share information with your team to counter adaptive movement strategies.
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_206:
· Place portals to scout and choose the best time to teleport.
· Use portals to quickly reposition and disrupt the enemy’s strategy.
· Keep an eye on the mid-lane to avoid being flanked.
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_TeamMatch_Tri:
· Players may switch characters at anytime during battle.
· During the Final Showdown, a Reverstring Storm will appear on the map. Avoid it at all costs.
· Gain a tactical item for every double kill.
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_203:
- Keep control of the center to ensure you can rotate and support your teammates.
- Shuffle between the low-gravity areas to disrupt enemy movements.
- Don't get caught in the wind tunnel. Keep a close eye out for enemies.
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_204:
- Improve your stringification skills to stay out of the water.
- Make sure to avoid the enemy's field of view, especially in open areas.
- Keep a close eye on the enemy's movements. Don't get flanked!
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_Zombie:
- Card buff mechanism is enabled.
- Superstrings start with passive skills unlocked.
- Crystallines killed by Ninjatos cannot be revived.
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_MineMatch:
· Ultimates require more points to activate.
· Adjust the String Energy Network while in your Warehouse Zone or waiting to respawn.
· Carry more Crystals during battles for stronger buffs.
· Deposit Crystals into the Ore Storage to earn ultimate points and String Energy Points.
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_TeamMatch:
- Weapon stats can be customized
- Earn tactical items with kill streaks
- Fixed respawn locations
- Switch characters anytime; active skills and ultimates are disabled
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_201:
- When gliding, you can strafe between tall buildings.
- Wall-slide to flank the enemy and hit them where they least expect it!
- Use the smoke grenade to cover your team while planting the bomb.
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_Escort:
· Approach or stick on the payload to advance it forward.
· Adjust the String Energy Network while in the Safe Zone or waiting to respawn.
· Team members will respawn together periodically.
ST_MapCfg.Thumb3_Desc_205:
· With three bomb sites, coordinating with your team is key to victory.
· Take advantage of the map by staying mobile.
· Pay close attention to the enemy's movements.
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_201: The Scissors have launched an attack on a business district under P.U.S control.
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_202: The Scissors detonated a bomb at the port and took advantage of the ensuing chaos to attack the nearby P.U.S Crystal Purification Center.
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_206: The Scissors make a bold entrance into the ruins.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_630: The Scissors have accepted an urgent contract to transport a payload to an event site in Snowveil District, Preton. However, P.U.S intercepts their communication and sets up a defensive perimeter along the route...
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_204: The Scissors have disrupted preparations for the Bablo Crystal Conference by force!
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_205: The Scissors have thwarted P.U.S' plans.
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_200: The Scissors plan to destroy the superstring weapons hidden in this P.U.S base.
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_207: The Scissors are attempting to destroy the dungeon.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_629: The Scissors have reached Jaksaa, a 2D computing facility. Now that P.U.S has gotten involved, escorting the payload has become a much more arduous task.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_1001: Strinova Guide at your service. Please do not try gliding after drinking Bablo sparkling water.
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_Zombie: A War for Survival in the Face of Crises
ST_MapCfg.Desc_207: Deep within the rift of the Seeda Peninsula, Ocarnus stands as a key historical relic, having witnessed eras of turmoil. Now, with the dormant Bablo lifeform nearing a final awakening, could a new crisis be on the horizon?
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_MineMatch: Tactical Play on Crystal Mining Fields
ST_MapCfg.Desc_11003: Located in northern Strian, the Polar Research Institute operates under P.U.S. jurisdiction as a center for mimetic environment research. The team is tackling the Outbreak crisis, but a new threat is rising...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_205: Located in the western corner of Preton, Cauchy Street is crisscrossed by cargo tracks that deliver crucial supplies to the entire city. Currently, P.U.S has breached The Scissors' defenses and have intercepted the cargo trains...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_405: Located in the western corner of Preton, Cauchy Street is crisscrossed by cargo tracks that deliver crucial supplies to the entire city. Currently, P.U.S has breached The Scissors' defenses and have intercepted the cargo trains...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_202: Located in Neutroville and adjacent to the Sea of Dreams, Port Euler is Strinova's largest Bablo energy transport and trade port.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_402: Located in Neutroville and adjacent to the Sea of Dreams, Port Euler is Strinova's largest Bablo energy transport and trade port.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_628: P.U.S set a trap at the Windy Town Exhibition, trapping The Scissors in a mind prison known as the Departure Zone. The only way for The Scissors to escape is by following rules and advancing the payload...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_118: The underwater power plant is a crucial project for Port Euler. It is equipped with P.U.S's latest high-efficiency hydroelectric generators, capable of fully meeting the energy needs of the Purification Center.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_631: Tyve Oasis, located in the Seeda Peninsula's Migo River Basin, is a tourist hotspot. Generations of settlers built this town around the ancient Komos Tower. As part of a strategic long-term plan for Seeda Peninsula, The Scissors are deploying a hacking device deep into the heart of the oasis...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_11001: Loch District sits on the outskirts of Preton City, close to the True Wilderness, and was one of the first areas affected by the Outbreak crisis.
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_TeamMatch: A chaotic battle, filled with peril.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_770: Located at the intersection of the True Wilderness and the city, Dirac Mine was the first Bablo Crystal extraction site designated by P.U.S. However, with the invasion of rival factions, the area has now plunged into chaos...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_115: Located on the outskirts of Strian and adjacent to Windy Town, Pier Town is a key maritime transit hub in the region.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_206: Cosmite lies nestled within the vast desert of the Seeda Peninsula. Once the first settlement for humanity in the New World, it faded into obscurity over time. It wasn't until the discovery by P.U.S and The Scissors that this relic resurfaced...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_203: Located on the cliff outside of Base S12, Space Lab has been a key part of The Scissors' spacetime travel research efforts. Now that the lab has fallen into P.U.S' hands, The Scissors have dispatched a task force to prevent any confidential information from being leaked...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_403: Located on the cliff outside of Base S12, Space Lab has been a key part of The Scissors' spacetime travel research efforts. Now that the lab has fallen into P.U.S' hands, The Scissors have dispatched a task force to prevent any confidential information from being leaked...
ST_MapCfg.World_View_Desc_TeamMatch_Tri: Small teams battle against each other for their own agenda.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_113: Boasting a long and storied history, Blossom Dojo is located in the southwest of Area 88. Quiet and tranquil, it has attracted no shortage of master archers.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_110: Located in the western corner of Eletron City, Wright Campus is the permanent venue for the Field Theory and Stringification Conference. The campus boasts beautiful surroundings and an open, scholarly atmosphere.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_11002: The ancient city of Ghannak, nestled in the northern Seeda Peninsula, lures adventurers into its realm of eternal night. Now, Crystallines swarm the area, escalating the danger to new extremes.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_10020: The range is a specialized virtual space where superstrings can practice freely.
ST_MapCfg.Desc_204: Located in downtown Strian, Windy Town is one of the most popular resorts in Strinova. The town is currently preparing to hold the Bablo Crystal Technology Exhibition, but with P.U.S and The Scissors getting involved, things have gotten a lot more “interesting”...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_414: Located in downtown Strian, Windy Town is one of the most popular resorts in Strinova. The town is currently preparing to hold the Bablo Crystal Technology Exhibition, but with P.U.S and The Scissors getting involved, things have gotten a lot more “interesting”...
ST_MapCfg.Desc_111: District Arcadia is located on the outskirts of Neutroville, right next to Area 88. This immersive entertainment district frequently holds esports events and hosts brand pop-up stores.

ST_Setting_MB.VoiceEffect_2:
Choose how in-game sounds like footsteps, gunfire, and ability effects are presented, with each option offering different 3D spatial effects.
 
HRTF: 3D surround sound via headphones with sound distinguished between the front and rear. Make sure to disable other 3D sound programs when using HRTF. 
 
7.1 Surround Sound: If supported, expands the sound field to distinguish sounds from all directions for more precise sound localization. 
 
Dolby Atmos: If your device or environment supports it, experience immersive Dolby Atmos sound that envelopes from above and around you, placing you at the forefront of the game. Enjoy an intense and thrilling atmosphere as if you're transported into the game itself.
ST_Setting_MB.VoiceEffect_Mobile_2:
Choose how in-game sounds like footsteps, gunfire, and ability effects are presented, with each option offering different 3D spatial effects.
 
HRTF: 3D surround sound via headphones with sound distinguished between the front and rear. Make sure to disable other 3D sound programs when using HRTF. 
 
7.1 Surround Sound: If supported, expands the sound field to distinguish sounds from all directions for more precise sound localization. 
 
Dolby Atmos: If your device or environment supports it, experience immersive Dolby Atmos sound that envelopes from above and around you, placing you at the forefront of the game. Enjoy an intense and thrilling atmosphere as if you're transported into the game itself.
ST_Setting_MB.SpatialAudioTypeMB_2:
Use spatial audio effects for in-game sounds.

If you encounter audio lag, try lowering the spatial audio setting. If you can't hear gunshots or footsteps, there may be a hardware compatibility issue. Try disabling spatial audio or switching to HRTF.
ST_Setting_MB.SpatialAudioType_2:
Use spatial audio effects for in-game sounds.

If you encounter audio lag, you may be able to resolve the issue by lowering the spatial audio.
If you cannot hear gunshots, footsteps, and/or enemy ultimate voice lines, there may be compatibility issues. Try disabling spatial audio or changing the audio output to stereo or HRTF.
ST_Setting_MB.SmartAutoInWall_2:
Determine how the character will stringify and wall-stick when near a valid wall.
Forward wall-stick: When the character is near a valid wall and continues to move forward, they will automatically wall-stick after a short delay.
Left wall-stick: When the character is near a valid wall, a wall-stick indicator will appear above the joystick. Drag the joystick to this indicator to auto wall-stick (when possible).
Manual wall-stick: You must tap a separate button to wall-stick.
ST_Setting_MB.FlashBangColor_2: Choose the screen effect color for flashbangs.
ST_Setting_MB.Switch_ClickedSmiteMode_2:
Toggle how to use melee weapon heavy attacks.
Fixed Button: Press the fire button for light attacks and the secondary fire button for heavy attacks.
Toggle: Press the secondary fire button to toggle between light and heavy attacks when using the fire button.
ST_Setting_MB.WindowsAudioAPI_2:
Select the underlying API for the audio system (effective after restarting the game).
Auto-select: Tries XAudio2, WASAPI, and DirectSound in sequence, using the first supported API.

If you encounter audio issues that persist after adjusting spatial audio and output settings, there may be system or hardware compatibility problems. Switching the audio API configuration may resolve the issue.
ST_Setting_MB.Switch_KeyUpClose_2: Some instant skills trigger on key release to prevent activating multiple skills at once (recommended for combo skills)
ST_Setting_MB.ButtonStyle_SprintMode_2:
Hold: When auto sprint is disabled, hold the sprint button to sprint and release to walk. When auto sprint is enabled, hold the sprint button to walk and release to sprint.

Toggle: Your character initially moves according to the auto sprint setting. Press sprint key to switch between walk and sprint. The toggle remains even after the character stops moving.
ST_Setting_MB.ButtonStyle_MBSideMode_2:
Hold: Hold to sidestep.
Toggle: Press to toggle sidestep.
ST_Setting_MB.ButtonStyle_MBFlyMode_2:
Hold: Hold to maintain glide.
Toggle: Press to toggle glide.
ST_Setting_MB.Switch_TeamChat_2: The team voice channel includes all 5 members of your team.

ST_UIActivities.Text_Info_1_Text:
*All rewards may undergo quality updates. Please refer to the final release version.
*Make sure to use the same account when the game officially launches.
ST_UIActivities.TxtDuration_Text:
1. During the event, complete quests to earn Battle Pass experience rewards.
2. During the event, the Experience Store unlocks once your Battle Pass experience is full.
3. During the event, after your Battle Pass experience is full, your extra experience can be used to change items in the Experience Store.
4. When the event ends, your remaining experience will be converted to Dream Tokens and sent to you via mail.
ST_UIActivities.RichTextBlock_210_Text:
<Chat-Self>Strinova Closed Beta Test: Superstring Rewards, </><Rank-Red>select a reward for time-warping, and it will be yours when the game officially launches!</>

Join Meredith and complete the seven-day quest to receive your reward on the <Rank-Red>eighth day</>!
ST_UIActivities.TxtShopDesc_Text: <Outline_Yellow16>During the event,</> your extra Battle Pass experience can be exchanged for the following items
ST_UIActivities.2024Anniversary_Text_6: You can exchange play points for souvenirs.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_138_Text: Navigators who top up will receive an extra Starter Pack. Check your rewards!
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_6_Text_1: The invitation code for early entry can only be obtained by Navigators who have mastered stringification.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_2_Text: During the event, log in each day to claim a reward. Collect all rewards by logging in for 7 days. After collecting all rewards, the event ends on the next login. Rewards are automatically claimed, so be sure to check them.
ST_UIActivities.Alienware_Describe:
Complete daily challenges to earn event points and unlock rewards.
Resets daily at {refreshTime}.
ST_UIActivities.FirstChargeRules_Content_1: Receive a Starter Pack after completing your first top-up of any amount.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_RoleFree_Text: Free to use for all roles
ST_UIActivities.2024Anniversary_Text_7: Collect play points to unlock stories.
ST_UIActivities.LimitedSale_Content:
Spring Market: Tons of skins are back and available for purchase with Bablo Crystals. Navigators can buy them directly at [CUSTOMIZE] → [OUTFIT].
[DAILY PICKS] offers a 20% discount on selected skins from this event.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_7_Text: Welcome to Strinova, we wish you a wonderful gaming experience.
ST_UIActivities.BindDiscord_Content1:
Step 1: Click the button to join the Strinova Discord server
Step 2: Find #bot-command Channel and type /link
Step 3: Link your account and return to this event page to claim rewards
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_7_Text_1: Every Navigator may assist up to three friends in entering Strinova.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_313_Text: Open daily for 7 days to obtain all rewards
ST_UIActivities.Text_Info_Text: Log in daily to unlock one reward each day, for up to 7 rewards in total. On the eighth day, you can choose one item to time-warp and receive it when the game officially launches.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_48_Text: Tap to claim your daily Bablo Crystal rewards
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_5_Text: Strinova is still under construction and there may be instability and reverse-stringification areas.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_233_Text: The item has been sent to your future account
ST_UIActivities.Txt_ActivityDesc_Text: Complete the quest to generate an activation code to invite a friend to stringify and enter the world of Strinova!
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_6_Text: Every beat of the notes guides us closer to each other.

ST_UIActivities2025CNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_90_Text: 1. During the event, participate in matches (excluding Custom mode) to earn Lucky Coins after each match.
ST_UIActivities2025CNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_Text: 2. There are 5 types of Lucky Coins, and you can earn up to 10 each day.
ST_UIActivities2025CNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_2_Text: 4. Lucky Coins can be exchanged with eligible friends, up to 5 times daily.
ST_UIActivities2025CNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_4_Text: 6. Friend data may have a few minutes delay.
ST_UIActivities2025CNYCollectBlessings.TextBlock_4_Text: a. In Escort mode, the payload periodically shoots out Lucky Coins. Approach a Lucky Coin to collect it.
ST_UIActivities2025CNYCollectBlessings.TextBlock_5_Text: b. In other modes, different types and amounts of Lucky Coins drop randomly at the end of a match.
ST_UIActivities2025CNYCollectBlessings.MainPage_Content: To celebrate the holidays, the Urbino Business Alliance has prepared surprise gifts for the residents of Strinova.

ST_UIActivitiesBiochemical.Explain_Text5:
1. During the event, participate in any mode except Custom to earn up to 10 Mind Crystals per day.
2. While playing Outbreak mode, pick up Supply Crates or Evo Crystals for a chance to get up to 10 Reflection Crystals per day.
3. Use Mind and Reflection Crystals in the Intel Center to gain Intel EXP and boost your Intel Level.
4. Each Intel Level upgrade grants Upgrade Supplies, potentially containing: Memory Sequence x1 (5%), Basestring x20 (5%), Basestring x10 (10%), Dream Token x50 (30%), Dream Token x20 (50%).
5. In the Intel Center, exchange Intel EXP with friends. Gift 50 Intel EXP each time, up to 100 times daily, without using your own Intel EXP, and receive up to 10 times.
6. Increase your Intel Level to unlock event stories. Read them in Investigation Reports to earn extra rewards.
7. Boost your Intel Level or complete quests to claim rewards at the Supply Center.
8. After reaching the max Intel Level, continue earning Intel EXP for more Upgrade Supplies.

<White12_Medium>Upgrade Supply</>

ST_UIActivitiesBiochemical.HoveredTips_1:

ST_UIActivitiesBiochemical.Achieves_Text1: Born from the unusual amidst the ordinary.
ST_UIActivitiesBiochemical.Explain_Text6:
A bombing orchestrated by The Scissors destroyed the Komos Tower in Preton, blurring the boundaries between the True Wilderness and the Stable Zone. Urbino has been entrusted with the reconstruction and repair effort, during which sightings of large creatures have been reported, and workforce members have gone missing. A new, aggressive, infectious force—the Crystallines—have emerged!

The P.U.S. task force quickly sealed off the area and launched a joint operation with Urbino to eliminate the threat. When a creature from the Hive is defeated, its consciousness separates and returns to a backup Superstring form. These consciousness fragments reveal insights into the history of the world and the origins of the Crystallines.

The Grove family, represented by Audrey, has extended an invitation to the Navigator to help collect these consciousness fragments on behalf of Urbino.

ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_6_Text1:
Before you choose to fight for the future on your own terms, you may require some assistance and guidance.
This is the reason why the Lumos Initiative was created.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_4_Text1:
You have taken the crucial first in combat. This is a commendable effort.
We have faith that you will play an important role in the future of Strinova.

ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_21_Text: Only recruits at or under Lv. 5 can be hired.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_12_Text: Before you choose for fight for the future on your own terms, you may require some assistance and guidance. This is the reason why the Lumos Initiative was created.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_6_Text: You are battle-hardened in Strinova. At the same time, there are many who do not yet possess the strength and courage to fight alone.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_11_Text: You have taken the crucial first in combat. This is a commendable effort. We have faith that you will play an important role in the future of Strinova.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_3_Text3: You can select a Recruitment Password. After changing passwords, your old password will no longer work.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_10_Text: This message indicates that you have been selected as a candidate for the Lumos Initiative.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_4_Text: While you were away, Strinova has undergone a lot of changes. As you explore, we have prepared for you a series of training that will help you familiarize yourself with combat.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_8_Text1: Complete all recruit quests and obtain exclusive event rewards
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_14_Text: Find an instructor and obtain a recruitment password, opening the door to a new world.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_2_Text: Navigator, you have been chosen as an instructor for the Lumos Initiative.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_26_Text1: Once you reach Strinova Lv. 20, after completing all recruit quests and claiming the rewards, you may become an instructor and start recruiting.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_3_Text1: We're sending you this message as we've detected that your communication signal has been re-activated. Welcome back to Strinova.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_3_Text: Our goal is to give everyone a fair chance to decide their own destiny. The Lumos Initiative was born to inspire and guide people, no matter what they ultimately choose to fight for.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_4_Text2: We are confident of your success in this quest! Worry not. The Lumos Initiative has prepared ample supplies both for you and any helpers, as you shall see when you meet her soon.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_23_Text: If a recruit Cadet is lost, the relationship will be unbound, but the quest progress will be kept.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.TextBlock_3_Text2: When a new Cadet does not log in for 30 days in total, they will be removed from the Cadets list. The progress of completed and ongoing quests will not be affected.
ST_UIActivitiesFission.LookingForwardToWorkingWithYouAgain: Looking forward to working with you again.

ST_UIActivitiesHallomas.ExplainContent1:
It's almost time for the annual Spookfest! To celebrate and boost sales, Urbino is hosting a three-day street parade. Participants are encouraged to dress up as their favorite characters, and the audience will vote to decide which lucky participant wins a mysterious gift.

Show off for a chance to win awesome rewards. Three lively days are coming to Commercial Street!

But before the celebration begins, something peculiar happens. Spectators report spotting a real ghost among the parade participants. Festival-goers grow uneasy, worried about whether the parade can still proceed as planned. As a staff member, it's your job to identify the "ghost" from a list of suspects...
ST_UIActivitiesHallomas.Rule4: Unlocked event stories will be saved in the Comms for future updates. Navigators can review them anytime.
ST_UIActivitiesHallomas.Rule2: Use Pumpkin Lollipops in Fright Night to unlock event stories. Read them to obtain rewards.

ST_UIActivitiesHallomas.Rule5: Unused Pumpkin Lollipops will be automatically converted and sent via mail after the event.

ST_UIActivitiesHallomas.Rule3: Unlock all stories to access the Spooky Sweet Shop, where you can exchange Pumpkin Lollipops for Basestring rewards.

ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_1_Text: To promote her café, Audrey embraced the Navigator's suggestion by wearing a maid outfit as a promotional strategy.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_5_Text1: Following the Navigator's advice, Yvette decided to connect with a wide range of people. Her research revealed that people in service roles, such as maids, are quite effective.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_4_Text: The Navigator is organizing a maid-themed idol event for Kanami.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.YvetteWordMap_2: Some rude guests do cause trouble, but I don't think it's a big deal. It's all research at the end of the day, and Fay makes sure they behave.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.MaidSelectedItem_Audrey_bp_maidDesc: To promote a café under her management, Audrey heeds the Navigator's advice, putting on a maid outfit as a method of promotion.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.KanamiWordMap_2: This outfit? It's my way of saying thanks for always having my back! Keep cheering me on, and I'll keep dazzling you~!
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.AudreyWordMap_2: W-What? Handling guests is... of course, something I can manage just fine...
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.MaidSelectedItem_Yvette_bp_maidDesc: Heeding the Navigator's advice, Yvette has decided to get to know people of all kinds. Based on her research, she has concluded that service personnel such as maids seem to be more useful.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.AudreyWordMap_3: As my strategist, it's only fair that you receive the best service. After all, providing excellent assistance is a maid's responsibility, right?
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.KanamiWordMap_3: Hmm~ The response has been fantastic! How about I add a maid outfit to my next idol event? What do you think?
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_40_Text: Complete superstring quests to unlock exclusive rewards.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_5_Text: You have completed all of Yvette's quests. Go take a photo of her!
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_20_Text: You have completed all of Audrey's quests. Go take a photo of her!
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_4_Text1: You have completed all of Kanami's quests. Go take a photo of her!
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.MaidSelectedItem_Kanami_bp_maidDesc: The Navigator is organizing a maid-themed Kanami Idol event.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.AudreyWordMap_1: Go ahead, take a good look! B-But make sure to try our new coffee... please?
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.YvetteWordMap_3: I want to learn more about people... especially you, Navigator.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.YvetteWordMap_1: I'm... doing what you suggested, Navigator. I believe studying the service industry, such as by being a maid, might be more fitting for my research.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.KanamiWordMap_1: Welcome back, Navigator. You've been working hard~

ST_UIActivitiesMarineOrganism.ExplainContent3:
1. Participate in the [Adventure Plan] to collect [Coral Branches].
       2. Collect [Coral Branches] to unlock [Treasure Hunter's Diary] stories and receive rewards the first time you read them.
       3. Perform a [Deep Sea Hunt] and spend [Coral branches] to get random items and drift bottle stories.
       4. Once you obtain all [Deep Sea Hunt] rewards, a new unlimited reward table will become available.
       5. Head to the [Bottled Tales] page to view your collected drift bottle stories.
ST_UIActivitiesMarineOrganism.ExplainContent1:
Surf the waves, build sandcastles, soak up the sun—create unforgettable memories.

Explore shipwrecks, uncover ruins, embark on daring quests—hunt for mysterious treasures.

The summer islands, far from the city's hustle and bustle, have become the hottest vacation spot and a treasure hunter's dream! Adventurers and tourists alike take on the roles of ancient sea creatures, face various trials, and piece together treasure maps to uncover legendary loot.

In this paradise of white sands and turquoise waves, what awaits you and the girls? Thrilling surprises or unexpected scares?

ST_UIActivitiesMeredith.TextBlock_1_Text:
Event Background
 The expedition team arrives at the edge of the True Wilderness, and their communication devices begin to flash.
 Intel shows a signal deep within the Wilderness, accompanied by a surge of crystal energy.
 It all feels like a carefully laid trap. But it’s too late to turn back now—there's something out there, whether energy or a lost soul.

Event Time
 TBD

Event Rules
 1. Complete quests during the event to earn Energy Points and recharge the pyramid.
 2. When the pyramid reaches a certain Energy level, you have a chance to receive rewards and clues.
 3. At 100% Energy, obtain a Superstring Selection Gift Box.
 4. After summoning and unlocking a Superstring, exchange remaining Energy Points for items.
 5. Daily quests refresh at 7:00 AM (UTC+0).
ST_UIActivitiesMeredith.HeadText_1_Text: Complete quests to collect energy. Reach 100% to unlock Meredith.
ST_UIActivitiesMeredith.TalkText_Text: I hope you can keep this a secret, especially since it involves... No, I mean... Just think of it as a scientist being too proud to admit that they're wrong

As fall approaches, the annual Fall Harvest Festival of Elitron is about to being. Everyone is invited to taste the delicacies brought by the rich produce of Strinova World, and fill their bellies during this joyful event.

Having been invited to join the feast, the Navigator spots Lawine all by herself in Elitron's shopping street. What interesting story will unfold from this encounter? What delicious surprises await?

ST_UIActivitiesNowYouSeeMe.TextBlock_157_Text:
Laurel Gallery is gearing up for an extraordinary concert featuring the renowned singer Kanami! Naturally, the Navigator was among the first to receive a VIP ticket signed by Kanami herself. Word has it that Kanami will also debut her magic act during the concert!

Meanwhile, Bai Mo invites the Navigator to the Twilight Auction, sponsored by the Bai Group, held in the Kidd Hall. It's rumored that the auction features unique treasures and collections that are valuable even to the Navigator!

With both irresistible events happening at the same time, which invitation will the Navigator choose? Given that both are at Laurel Gallery, attending half of each might just be possible...

ST_UIActivitiesSalon.OpenAfterAllCluesAreObtained: Opens once all clues are obtained.
ST_UIActivitiesSalon.TxtContent_Text:
Despite her intimidating aura, speaking with Flavia was surprisingly easy. However, I couldn't help but notice that she had been subtly controlling the subject of the conversation.
It was as if she was trying to tell me something.
“On a side note, there was this charming and mysterious woman who showed up at the bar after hours. I even managed to get her name.”
“I wonder... did that all happen, or was I just dreaming?”
Flavia smiled softly: “I don't want to get into the business of plugging one lie with another, so I'll tell the truth.”
“Please, don't hold back.”
Flavia lowered her eyes and shot a serious look at the poker table: “It wasn't me. The cards were already on the table when I arrived.
I'm simply trying to solve the mystery... care to join me?”
I couldn't say no.
ST_UIActivitiesSalon.TxtDesc_Text:
My eyes wandered around the bar before being quickly drawn to a woman sitting on a single sofa, playing poker.
Everything about her screamed “mysterious”, from the smile on her lips and her hidden gaze
to her figure flickering under the light. Could this be my client?

ST_UIApartmentInformation.TextBlock_Content_Text: I'm just an ordinary girl with nothing special. Growing up in a small town, my parents were always busy. I had no toys, nor friends to hang out with. I felt lonely all the time. But later on, I discovered anime and video games! Albeit still alone, I was no longer lonely. Anime and video games showed a whole new world full of wonders! It was only natural for me to venture into Strinova by myself. Never could I imagine that I was entering a two-dimensional world. I made a vow to protect, so I volunteered to become a P.U.S investigator!

ST_UIAuth.RichTextBlock_37_Text:
To protect the physical and mental health of minors, and in accordance with the “Notice on Further Strengthening the Management and Preventing Minors from Indulging in Online Games” issued by the National Press and Publication Administration, here are some of the rules:

1. Users who have not completed identity verification are not allowed to play the game.

2. Minors are only allowed to play the game <Division_Type>during the hours from 8 p.m. to 9 p.m. on Fridays, Saturdays, Sundays, and public holidays</>.

3. Players under <Division_Type>8 years of age</> are not allowed to top up. Players aged <Division_Type>8 and above but under 16 years of age</> are limited to a maximum single top-up amount of <Division_Type>50</> and a monthly cumulative top-up amount of <Division_Type>200</>. Players aged <Division_Type>16 and above</> but <Division_Type>under 18 years of age</> are limited to a maximum single top-up amount of <Division_Type>100</> and a monthly cumulative top-up amount of <Division_Type>400</>.

ST_UIAuth.Text_3_Text: According to the “Notice on Preventing Minors from Indulging in Online Games” issued by the National Press and Publication Administration, all online game users are required to register their game accounts using valid identification. ST_UICareerCareerRank.Txt_RankTips_Text: 1. The Server-wide Ranked and Challenge Leaderboards display the top 1,000 players in Quark and above. The top 100 players appear in the Team Deathmatch, Crystal Scramble, Escort, and Outbreak leaderboards. All rankings refresh hourly.
ST_UICareerCareerRank.TextBlock_121_Text: 2. Go to System Settings > Basic to configure your location privacy.
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_2_ContentText1:
<Black22>1. The basic star rules remain the same: winning team gains 1 star, losing team loses 1 star. Strinovium Points are an additional star-gaining rule.</>

<Black22>2. After a match, regardless of the outcome, you gain Strinovium Points. Strinovium Points = Mode Score + Win Streak Bonus + Match Ranking Bonus + Skill Bonus (if your team's overall skill is above the average for that rank).</>

<Black22>3. Star Protection: When your Strinovium Points reach a certain threshold, Star Protection activates. If you lose a Ranked Match, it will deduct the corresponding amount of Strinovium Points instead of losing a star. The points consumed for Star Protection increase with Rank.</>

<Black22>4. Bonus Star: When your Strinovium Points hit the cap, winning another Ranked Match will consume some of your current Strinovium Points and add 1 star. The points consumed for this are equal to the Star Protection points for your current Rank.</>

<Black22>5. Match Ranking Bonus: 1st place (5 points), 2nd place (4 points), 3rd place (4 points), 4th place (3 points), 5th place (3 points).</>

<Black22>6. Win Streak Bonus: 1 win (3 points), 2 wins (8 points), 3 wins (13 points), 4 wins (18 points), 5 wins and above (23 points).</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.RichTextBlock_37_Text: <Black22>The ranked mode is the most challenging mode of Strinova. Every season, players who dare to take the challenge will receive epic rewards. You have to reach Lv. 5 and own at least 5 heroes to play the ranked mode. Keep leveling up and unlocking heroes, and you can start your legendary journey.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_1_ContentText: <Black22>In ranked mode, you earn a star for each victory and lose a star for each defeat by default. After your star count is full, earning another star increases your division or rank. When you have no stars left, losing another star demotes you to the next division or rank.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_5_ContentText: <Black22>During each season, once you reach a certain rank, you can obtain the corresponding rewards. For details on rewards and their corresponding rank, please visit the Season Rewards page.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_ContentText1:
<Black22>Players are assigned to one of several ranked divisions, broadly indicative of a player's skill level.</>
<Black22>Division lowest to highest are: Substance, Molecule, Atom, Quark, Origin Stringification, Superstring, Strinova.</> <Black22>The Substance to the Superstring divisions are further subdivided into grades, each accompanied by a number of stars. See here for further details in the Rank Map.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_3_ContentText:
<Black22>When a player reaches Strinova, their maximum star limit will be increased to 9,999. The system performs a check every hour, and if a player has not played any ranked matches during the previous 7 days, they will lose 1 star.</>
<Black22>The server updates the rankings of all players every hour. The top players in the rank of Strinova will be listed on the leaderboard. This information will be sent to all the players on the server.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_4_ContentText:
<Black22>Season Duration: Each season lasts for approximately three months.</>

<Black22>Your rank and division reset after the end of each season. After the previous season ends, everyone has a chance to start over. Your starting position in the new season will be determined by your highest rank from the previous season.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_1_ContentText1:
<Rank-Title>1.</> When your Strinovium Points reach a certain score, a portion of them will be deducted first to offset losing a star after a Ranked match loss.
<Rank-Title>2.</> When your Strinovium Points are at the maximum limit, winning a Ranked match will consume some points to grant an extra star.
<Rank-Title>3.</> Each rank has different Strinovium Points limits, and the amount deducted for losses or consumed for wins varies.


<Rank-Title>Bonus Scores:</>
<Rank-Title>1. No AFK:</> 3 points.
<Rank-Title>2. Match Score Rankings:</> Earn Strinovium Points based on your score ranking within your team. <Rank-Red>1st place:</> 24 points, <Rank-Red>2nd place:</> 18 points, <Rank-Red>3rd place:</> 13 points, <Rank-Red>4th place:</> 9 points, <Rank-Red>5th place:</> 6 points.
<Rank-Title>3. Win Streaks:</> <Rank-Red>1 win:</> 3 points, <Rank-Red>2 wins:</> 8 points, <Rank-Red>3 wins:</> 13 points, <Rank-Red>4 wins:</> 18 points, <Rank-Red>5+ wins:</> 23 points.
<Rank-Title>4. Skill Compensation:</> 10 points. Awarded when your rank is significantly lower than the enemy team's average, regardless of the outcome.
<Rank-Title>5. Effort Compensation:</> 50 points. Given to outstanding players in case of defeat or a draw.
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_2_ContentText:
<Rank-Title>1.</> Upon reaching Superstring rank, Ranked matches switch to a points system. Points increase or decrease based on performance and outcome after each match.
<Rank-Title>2.</> On promotion from Quark to Superstring rank, Strinovium Points convert to Superstring Points at a <Rank-Red>20:1</> ratio.
<Rank-Title>3.</> If Superstring Points fall to 0, your first loss triggers rank protection. Another loss will demote you to Quark I.
<Rank-Title>4.</> If you don't play a Ranked match for <Rank-Red>7 consecutive days</>, you'll lose 30 Superstring Points, down to a minimum of 0.
<Rank-Title>5.</> Once you reach 200 Superstring Points, ranking in the top 500 promotes you to Singularity rank. Falling out of the top 500 demotes you back to Superstring rank.
<Rank-Title>6.</> Superstring and Singularity ranked players can only queue solo or as a duo.
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_ContentText:
<Rank-Title>Participation Rules:</> Reach <Rank-Red>Lv. 10</> to unlock ranked matches.
<Rank-Title>Season Duration:</> Each season lasts around 2 months. At the end of the season, rewards are based on the highest rank achieved. A new season begins with placement matches to determine your initial rank.
<Rank-Title>Rank Structure:</> There are 9 major ranks, each with various divisions and Strinovium Points thresholds.
<Rank-Title>Promotion and Demotion:</> Earn a promotion after filling all stars in a division and winning one more match, gaining an extra star. Exceptional Navigators may skip a sub-rank.
Demotion occurs after losing all stars in a division and one additional loss.
<Rank-Title>Rank Protection:</> Players in the Substance or Molecule rank will not lose any stars after losses. Players in the Proton rank will not be demoted after losing all stars in a division.

The Escort leaderboard shows the top 100 players with at least 500 kills/assists. The Outbreak leaderboard shows players with at least 10 wins and damage ≥ 100,000. All rankings refresh hourly.

ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP8_Card1_Content: A girl who dreams of breaking the shackles of fate, she is currently under special observation as a user of a new String Body.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP7_Card1_Content: A talented master perfumer. With her help, the Scissors seem to have gained a new lease of life.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP10_Card1_Content: A terrifying assassin akin to the Grim Reaper. Once she lays her eyes on you, escape is impossible.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP9_Card1_Content: A cheerful, straightforward, and reliable civil engineer. She works to help maintain the order established by P.U.S.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP8_Card2_Content: To ensure that the Snowveil District Music Festival goes smoothly, The Scissors are carrying out an urgent transport mission...
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP8_Card3_Content: The Urbino Business Alliance is hosting a celebration, inviting everyone to dress as their favorite character for a night parade. But strange things keep happening... Could something unusual have slipped into the festivities?
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP7_Card3_Content: With a mysterious letter, you became the new employer of the "Shark". How does one become stronger? What is true strength? These questions are awaiting your answer.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.Text_RankDesc_Text: Your excellent performance has made you stand out among many mighty warriors. Your future breakthrough will surely revolutionize the entire competitive scene.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP7_Card2_Content: Looking back, the New Dimensions Initiative guided humans to Strinova and built a new home in the vast expanse...
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP10_Card2_Content: In the face of disaster, no matter who is in control, we are all bound by fate.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_Text: Rewards will be sent out via mail
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP101_Card2_Content: A masked high school girl, with flames dancing at her fingertips, silently safeguards the streets of Preton.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP9_Card3_Content: Enjoy lively scenes during this pleasant time of the year. Follow the cheerful drumbeats and participate in a series of New Year-themed events!
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP10_Card4_Content: The Soul Sovereign Warrant progress is now live. Advanced Warrant rewards include outfits: Kokona - Relic Hunter and Mara - Soul Seeker. The Advanced Warrant PLUS includes the chip case: Hand of Dominion.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP7_Card4_Content: Scarlet Awakening Warrant is now available. Advanced Warrant rewards include: Fragrans - Desert Explorer and Eika - Fire Dancer. Advanced Warrant Plus also grants an exclusive case reward: V-06 Fragrance Interwoven.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP8_Card4_Content: Corrosive Genesis Warrant is now available. Advanced Warrant rewards include: Yugiri - Feather Dancer and Flavia - Special Agent. Advanced Warrant Plus also grants an exclusive case reward: W-02 Spiral Soul.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP10_Card3_Content: Unusual infections have recently emerged in the Preton area. The P.U.S urgently seeks Navigators to help uncover the truth behind the Outbreak crisis.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP9_Card2_Content: The underground city hidden between rifts suffers from a state of unending turmoil. Whenever one side falls from the peak, the other inevitably rises from the shadows. The process repeats until the day the truth is revealed...
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP9_Card4_Content: The Interstice Reconstruction Warrant is now available. Advanced Warrant rewards include Leona - Underground Survey and Ming - Goldsmith. Advanced Warrant PLUS also grants an exclusive case reward: D-09 Crystal Fissure

ST_UICareerNewSeasonSeasonAward.TheAwardIsSentByEmail1: ///  Rewards will be sent out via mail
ST_UICareerNewSeasonSeasonAward.TheAwardIsSentByEmail: Rewards will be sent out via mail

ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.Text_40_Text:
A lone shark seeking comfort, this new duelist prefers to be left alone.
 Reticent and hiding behind a mask, they are a skilled warrior, having studied the habits of sharks.
Make way for the shark!
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.Text_32_Text: Lawine frequently hits archery dojo. You can practice archery, watch flowers, and have tea here.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.Text_28_Text: As a result of Operation Crimson Blade, more explosion attacks have taken place in various locations. What hidden crisis lies among them...
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.Text_36_Text: Kokona, the inspector from PUS will meet with the Navigator in the dormitory. Kokona is a reliable veteran, but what is she like in real life? As the two get to know one another, the Navigator will uncover Kokona's hidden, softer side.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.Text_40_Text1: A free and lonely young shark, she is a duelist employed by Urbino. As long as the battle is interesting enough, she cares not for moral standards, eliminating all the targets.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_8_Text:
"Echoes" sound in the air, and streams of string vibration spread throughout the sky.
Under the cover of battle between P.U.S and The Scissors,
something quiet is happening.
What could it be? The curtain lifts.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_Text: In order to prevent PUS from stealing top secrets, The Scissors is determined to destroy crucial lab data...
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_5_Text:
Yvette meets you for the first time in the dorm!
Though little is known about this P.U.S researcher, her mysterious aura is intriguing. But with genuine interaction, even the thickest ice can melt.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_8_Text2:
Want to know the secrets behind the stage?
Then why not meet Kanami in person?
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_2_Text:
In the face of defeat, how can The Scissors reclaim the city's transit system
from Painting Utopia Security?
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_190_Text1:
An energetic high school student.
Adorned in a mask, she protects the streets of Preton
with the power of fire.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_8_Text1:
At The Scissors' invitation, the Astral Sanctuary
finds themselves a new city - Preton.
The calamity from 18 years past, the fate of P.U.S and The Scissors...
Everything will be decided here.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_2_Text2:
A new season has begun!
Earn your glory in the heat of battle!
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_5_Text1: Recently, Yvette has become hooked on Gomoku, and it just so happens you’re familiar with it too. Think you can beat her? Head to Yvette's dorm for a face-off!
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_190_Text:
A sunny young man dressed in fashionable attire,
this hacker travels the world with Urbino as his stage.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.SeasonPlotWhisperingDarkClouds: Season story: Whispers in the Dark
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_2_Text1:
This is a young and hip neighborhood.
Bai Mo enjoys skating here by the parkour route.
If you need to find him, this is the place!

ST_UILottery.Text_1_Text2: Base chance for [Legendary] drops: <Red>0.65%</>. Overall chance (inc. guarantee): <Red>1.7%</>. A Legendary Skin is guaranteed to drop within <Red>80</> draws. Draw count will be reset upon a Legendary drop. Use a <Red>Directed Sequence</> in Reconstruction to select your desired Legendary Set (Outfit/Weapon Skin). A Legendary drop in a Directed Sequence will always be of the chosen set. Obtain Directed Sequences in <Red>Season</> through Advanced Warrant PLUS. If you have chosen a Legendary Set and received the Legendary Outfit, your next Legendary drop will <Red>guaranteed</> to be a Weapon Skin, and vice versa. Epic Skin duplicates will drop only up to 2 times until all Epic Skins are drawn.
ST_UILottery.Text_1_Text1: [Legendary] Base chance: <Red>0.65%</>. Overall chance (inc. guarantee): <Red>1.7%</>. You are guaranteed a Legendary Skin after <Red>80</> draws. If you obtain a Legendary outfit from a draw, the next Legendary skin you obtain is <Red>guaranteed</> to be a weapon skin, and vice versa. Once you have both the Legendary outfit and weapon skin, this mechanic won’t carry over (each Cognitive Reconstruction season is calculated independently). The same Epic skin can be drawn twice until all Epic skins are drawn.

Summer_333_Lv_1.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId107: There's no need for such hostility. Art is boundless. I need you two to remain civil during the event!
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId107: See, Yvette's got a feeling for atmosphere.
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Yeah! It's “Summer Hits,” an annual music festival hosted by Urbino.
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId108: Why is she changing clothes for this occasion?
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Navigator, let's go enjoy the event together!
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row8_PlayerOption1: Feels like the Navigator's job is getting harder and harder...
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId107: I, Maddelena, am honored to be given responsibility for the event's layout and equipment together with the Navigator.
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId108: Think nothing of it. Protecting the city is P.U.S' job. I'll keep an eye on The Scissors.
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId107: As for maintaining order and controlling the audience... I leave it to you!
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row2_PlayerOption1: What kind of group is this?

Summer_333_Lv_2.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId108: You three, stop slacking around! Finish your work if you want to chat!
Summer_333_Lv_2.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Hey! You can't leave me alone with all this work.
Summer_333_Lv_2.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Oi, it's not like I'm the only one playing. Isn't everyone having fun?
Summer_333_Lv_2.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Sorry, sorry... I was busy collecting materials.
Summer_333_Lv_2.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId108: She doesn't reply to the group chat or my private messages. Where's she gone?
Summer_333_Lv_2.Row10_PlayerOption2: Stabbing me in the back now? You traitor!

Summer_333_Lv_3.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId108: No matter if it's Ming or that other guy.
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId107: You're just in time. I just got a bunch of skewers and takoyaki.
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Let's change the subject. The ice cream's going to melt.
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Thank you all for the hard work. I'll treat you guys today.
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId107: I know. This must be the feeling of loneliness that follows a big celebration.
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId108: I'm fine, just a little moved... The music of The Scissors is quite beautiful.
Summer_333_Lv_3.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId108: Looks like things are coming to an end...
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row5_PlayerOption1: It's probably not the main point, right?

Summer_333_Lv_4.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId107: But why has Nobunaga traveled so far?
Summer_333_Lv_4.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Navigator, Yvette, did you guys take a photo just now?
Summer_333_Lv_4.Row2_PlayerOption1: We would like to preserve this moment for eternity.
Summer_333_Lv_4.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId108: I'm just a steward. Maintaining order and monitoring The Scissors is my real job.
Summer_333_Lv_4.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId107: There we go! I'll hold onto this photo forever... it's my souvenir.

Summer_333_Lv_5.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId107: The one thing left to find is... the sea...
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Eh? What's wrong, Yvette? Have you been hiding with the Navigator all this time?
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId107: All good, then. I didn't expect that your abilities could be used like this...
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row21_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Just a small gift for everyone.
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Navigator, are you there? Have you seen Yvette? I can't find her at the beach or any of the food stalls.
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId108: Can you help me look, Navigator?
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId108: I'll ask around. You can head to the venue, Maddelena.
Summer_333_Lv_5.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId107: By the way, where's Yvette? I've been trying to find her for a while.
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Sigh... I can't find it anywhere. I'm getting worried.

Weapon.10101019_Tips:
The personalized Inspector paint job commemorates Michele's smile upon completing her first quest.

"Vanguard, ready for assault!"
Weapon.10404002_Tips: From the "Colorburst" series. Painted with streaks of different pigments. This firearm has a casual vibe, but it's overflowing with artistic flair.
Weapon.10404004_Tips: The Dreambreaker series combines patchy blues with occasional yellow fragments for a striking, shattered effect.
Weapon.10404005_Tips: The popular P.U.S-04 Vigilance adds a bright and distinctive finish to the P.U.S arsenal.
Weapon.10404003_Tips: The Thunderfire series seamlessly blends contemporary sleekness with retro orange-gray criss-crossing elements.
Weapon.10101002_Tips: The "Jungle" series features a primarily green gun body with subtle orange stripes. Not the prettiest tool in the shed, but it gets the job done.
Weapon.10102009_Tips: The Crisscross series features a dark base with intersecting lines, creating a dazzling display on the battlefield.
Weapon.10202002_Tips: The "Bushwhack" series camo design suits various combat environments.
Weapon.10108002_Tips: Embers series paint job featuring fiery orange and ashy gray.
Weapon.10102007_Tips: The "Faith" series features a black base with The Scissors emblem, showcasing the holder's unwavering resolve.
Weapon.10101026_Tips: The "Wave Surfer" series evokes beachside wave imagery with its minimalist blockish color design.
Weapon.10106111_Tips:
The special Spring Blessings edition of "Polaris," inspired by the motif "Ascendance," embodies the courage and determination Celestia has gradually built up through past hardships.

“For the patients, I won't back down anymore. This is what my predecessors taught me.”
Weapon.10106108_Tips:
A special customized version of the Polaris featuring a smoothed barrel that provides better grip. The embellished azure crystals also serve as an energy source for the firearm, enabling its bullets to race toward the targets like shooting stars.

【“This is no ordinary wishing star. It always flies toward my desired target.”】
Weapon.10106107_Tips:
A custom version of the Polaris, this model loses the original's cold weapon vibe, making it perfect for date nights. The scope also serves as a makeup mirror, enabling users to check their makeup anytime, anywhere.

"That was such a blast! I need to touch up my makeup... Heh.”
Weapon.10106106_Tips:
The specialized "Polaris" Model was a gift obtained from the Celestia Space Center. Designed to resemble a space station, it symbolizes humanity's dream of reaching the endless cosmos. It's no exaggeration to call this weapon a masterpiece of industrial art.

"To the endless sky, I offer my endless longing and love."
Weapon.10106201_Tips: This customized version of the Polaris features a striking scarlet rose in full bloom. A sword of knightly protection cuts through the design, telling a tale of beauty and valor.
Weapon.10106104_Tips:
Artistic Polaris model. References to fairy tales from old Earth reveal a surprising innocence in this weapon's designer.

【Wrapped in fragile dreams, a child's innocence beams. Kindness and purity, in our essence, gleams.】
Weapon.10403108_Tips:
A customized version of the "Champion" featuring enhanced sensitivity to light. Whether for photography or firing bullets, it performs in perfection.

“This moment is worth capturing, don't you think?”
Weapon.10403115_Tips: The Campus Open Day edition of the Champion is crafted per the student council vice president's request. It captures the academy's spirit while celebrating the Grove family's honor.
Weapon.10403111_Tips:
Crafted by Grove artisans, the "Champion" gala edition dazzles with a glass-like sheen and refreshing elegance. Perfect for making a statement at noble gatherings.

"Let's steal the spotlight."
Weapon.10403105_Tips:
The artistic custom version of "Champion" is inspired by old Earth's local folklore, vividly showcasing a deeply cultural aesthetic.

“In ignorance of bountiful years true,
Chasing the fox god, a myth in view,
Finding none but illusions and emptiness.”
Weapon.10111005_Tips: The Rebel series features a striking color contrast and a pattern design resembling a swift, powerful lightning bolt, perfectly capturing the spirit of rebellion and defiance.
Weapon.10106003_Tips: The "Multiverse" series features a Strinova-inspired design. Its simple yet intricate patterns exude a unique charm.
Weapon.10503101_Tips: A custom relic edition of Night Scythe, infused with folklore and traditional craftsmanship from the Seeda Peninsula, giving modern firearms the feel of ancient weaponry. Perhaps, those who wield it in battle can hear the blessings of ancient warriors.
Weapon.10503102_Tips:
The Gothic-style Night Scythe is the Undead Countess's cherished weapon. Adorned with thorns and a haunting ghostly visage, it's the embodiment of death itself.

"She invited me, so I've come. After all, her secrets intrigue me."
Weapon.10304103_Tips:
A customized version of the Judge. Under the setting sun, two cranes fly away, bidding farewell to the departed.

【The wings of the crane shall guide you home.】
Weapon.10304110_Tips:
The Inspector butler edition combines clean design with functional add-ons, providing a classy companion for when you're in the mood for a gentle buzz.

"Feel free to indulge; I've got your back."
Weapon.10304108_Tips:
A modified version of the "Judge" that incorporates chess pieces into the design, exclusively customized for chess show matches. Its sleek black and gold design makes it one of Nobunaga's favorites.

"I'll always be one move ahead of you."
Weapon.10304109_Tips:
A modified version of the Judge that incorporates chess pieces into the design, exclusively customized for chess show matches. Its sleek black and gold design makes it one of Nobunaga's favorites.

【"I will also think one move ahead of you."】
Weapon.10403107_Tips:
The customized "Manor's Grace" model's intricate design proves that high art can be just as deadly.

"Today's menu includes refreshing tea, delicious snacks, and a hearty supply of bullets."
Weapon.10106006_Tips: The "Chimera" series features an elegant orange mosaic design with deep and light tones, creating an artistic look.
Weapon.10501103_Tips:
The personalized "Beareas" model features a luxurious purple finish, a cute panda face, and a fierce soundwave effect when firing, symbolizing the passionate heart hidden beneath the user’s cold exterior.

“The taciturn girl pursed her lips tightly, letting out no sound. The music dancing with gunfire speaks for her.”
Weapon.10501110_Tips:
A customized version of Beareas, featuring camouflage painting by the host of a shooter game. Thanks to Yvette's stealth abilities, the compact Beareas is capable of delivering deadly strikes.

"Don't worry. They can't see me. I can take care of myself."
Weapon.10501109_Tips:
A special edition "Beareas" model, featuring a bold retro-artistic design. Inspired by luminous pearls, it’s set with these gems, giving it an extraordinary elegance.

"The pearl in your hand sparkles, dazzling ever more gloriously in the dark."
Weapon.10101003_Tips: From the "Colorburst" series. Painted with streaks of different pigments. This firearm has a casual vibe, but it's overflowing with artistic flair.
Weapon.10301105_Tips:
A customized Chroma model, ideal for outdoor combat. The gun's decor is inspired by animals Maddelena sketched in the wild, with cute expressions sure to bring a smile.

"This is my little companion. Why not say hello?"
Weapon.10301106_Tips:
The customized Chroma features a sleek space design enhanced with pink-purple energy beams symbolizing cosmic nebulae. These beams not only provide powerful energy for the weapon but also serve as excellent illuminators, making her creation shine brightly in the dark void of space.

“Let me adorn you to make you even more radiant.”
Weapon.10301111_Tips:
Specialized Chroma model. Adorned in bright green and decorated with cartoonish characters, this firearm is the perfect embodiment of Maddelena - romantic whimsy and childlike innocence.

【“It's funny, isn't it? When we're young, we couldn't wait to grow up, and now that we're grown, we wish we could be children again.'"】
Weapon.10301102_Tips:
A customized concept model of the Chroma. Inspired by Maddalena's aesthetics, it features her favorite bunny-themed elements.

"The last bunny rides a rocket into the depths of space.
In the vastness of stars, a spark rises into the unknown, marking the end of the glorious bunny civilization."
Weapon.10301110_Tips:
The classically designed romantic Chroma model features a tambourine on its body, ready to play a delightful dance tune.

“Don't fear my bullets; I'm just inviting you to join in a tambourine performance.”
Weapon.10301107_Tips:
This lightweight Chroma modification captures the essence of melody in its design. When fired, each shot resonates like a dynamic note.

“It's time to dance, my friends!”
Weapon.10104110_Tips:
A customized Shadow Assault model, featuring a sapphire seamlessly set into the hollow barrel, mirroring The Scissors' flawless plan.

"It's time!"
Weapon.10104107_Tips:
A customized version of the Shadow Assault featuring clever camouflage suitable for convert operations, embodying the concept of patience.

【“Hey, are the leaves talking?”】
Weapon.10104101_Tips:
The customized Shadow Assault features gilded edges like the setting sun and a crimson barrel resembling twilight clouds, symbolizing the splendid future people once hoped to see.

“Beautiful as the evening glow may be, it cannot escape the storm that cleanses the sky.”
Weapon.10104111_Tips:
The customized Shadow Assault features a concealed blade on its night-black frame, revealing its ruby-red edge only at critical moments, much like Lawine, who waits discreetly in the café, poised to act.

"There are unidentified people in the café... For your safety, I'll step in if necessary."
Weapon.10501106_Tips:
The customized "Frost Core" model features a delicate ice core encased in intricate metalwork. The bullets it fires are not scorching hot, but bone-chillingly cold.

“Rest assured, this bullet won't hurt you, but it may harm you in another way.”
Weapon.10111056_Tips: The Predator series features a bionic camo design, offering excellent camouflage in complex environments.
Weapon.10101056_Tips: The "Golden Surge" series, launched by Polaris Labs, features a dark gold pattern that combines a cool, flashy look with a powerful sense of metallic stability.
Weapon.10404101_Tips:
This retro Calibrator model replicates ancient murals from the "Dreams to Reality" historical exhibit. In your hands, it evokes an era of civilization’s brilliance.

"Under the beast's blessing, the pavilion shall stand tall."
Weapon.10404103_Tips:
The arcade-themed Calibrator draws inspiration from Leona's favorite childhood fighting game. She'll always remember the nostalgia of executing secret combos.

"Take this! It's the ultimate justice combo!"
Weapon.10106007_Tips: The "Prisma" series uses refractive fragmentation, with artistic purple shades evoking a kaleidoscopic feeling.
Weapon.10112105_Tips:
This retro Gambit model replicates ancient murals from the "Dreams to Reality" historical exhibit. In your hands, it evokes an era of civilization's brilliance.

"A celestial dance in timeless skies."
Weapon.10112104_Tips:
The customized stage version of the Gambit is adorned with a microphone and floating musical notes. When you suddenly hear Galatea's voice, you may have already stepped into her trap.

"Do you like my singing? You're in for a treat."
Weapon.10112103_Tips:
A reimagined "Gambit" with plentiful feather details for a less intimidating look. The user claims even its appearance plays into the deception.

"Dazzling and spellbinding!"
Weapon.10112107_Tips:
The arcade-themed Gambit features a gun skin designed to match the clothing, inspired by Galatea's favorite childhood space shooter game.

"I miss those childhood days playing games with my sister. She'd cry when she lost; it was adorable."
Weapon.10102003_Tips: The "Tidal Wave" series is composed of a series of blue modules meant to imitate the shape of a wave. It may lack the sound of the sea, but it remains a delight.
Weapon.10111055_Tips: The Graffiti series by Corridor Artisans creatively combines spray and street art elements, bringing Urbino's vibrant culture to life.
Weapon.10304002_Tips: From the Deep Lake series. Streaks of light and dark on resplendent cyan make for a restrained and brooding design.
Weapon.10101007_Tips: From the "Vivid" series. Made up of a variety of overlapping hexagonal color blocks, this firearm's streams of color give off the illusion of added firepower.
Weapon.10106004_Tips: The "Ardor" series, URB-00 custom edition, features vibrant, edgy colors that reflect the latest trends, and is a favorite among Urbino members.
Weapon.10112004_Tips: The "Ardor" series, URB-00 custom edition, features vibrant, edgy colors that reflect the latest trends, and is a favorite among Urbino members.
Weapon.10502104_Tips:
A customized version of Solo featuring crimson jamón ibérico. With the right condiments, it could almost capture an authentic Iberian flavor. Such a delicious appearance might just make enemies drop their guard.

“Careful. Don't fall for this deliciously charming trap.”
Weapon.10502102_Tips:
The customized Solo model features a dark theme with embedded crystals that gleam brightly even at night, exhibiting a mysterious deep blue shine like the sea.

"Wondering what I'm thinking? Why not... take a guess? It's a way to get to know each other."
Weapon.10502106_Tips:
A modified version of Solo. It features gradients, bright colors, and grids to emphasize a futuristic feel. The additional buttons are also highly favored by gamers.

"Press a key, get a sound, and hear your opponents' screams."
Weapon.10502107_Tips:
The modified Solo was Flavia's go-to weapon during her early missions with P.U.S. Its clean design echoes the precision of her successful missions.

"This gun sets the boundary—ten meters out is where danger starts."
Weapon.10502109_Tips:
The Gothic-style Solo showcases a spirit butterfly fluttering over bones, as if mourning the departed, despite being the very lure that led them to this graveyard.

"Rest in peace. There is no death - only eternal slumber."
Weapon.10502105_Tips:

They save lives not in the hope of praise, nor do they raise their guns to fight.
In front of them lies war, and behind them, peace.
Weapon_I18N.10403201_Tips:
A personalized Champion model with a pristine barrel, basking in the Grove family's glory and victories. Fervent flames flow through it, symbolizing Lord Grove's indomitable spirit.

To protect her family, the young girl took this gun onto the battlefield. Now, with the newly upgraded weapon in hand, there's composure and determination in her once-furrowed brow. The answers to those questions? As before, seek them through bullets.
Weapon_I18N.10403106_Tips:
A customized artistic version of the Champion, adorned with strings of the Guqin, concealing the pinnacle of technology under the classic design.

"In drifting clouds, her garments I find; in blossoms, her visage so fair.
She shines by the balustrade, caressed by the dew-laden air.
Should Jade Mountain's peak hold her not in view.
Then beneath the moon, on gemstone terrace, she'll appear anew."
Weapon_I18N.10403104_Tips:
The custom Champion design by Audrey incorporates four unique musical elements. Each string of notes plays the same melody with distinct tones.

"It's a piano, a saxophone, an old vinyl spinning in solitude, capturing the faded memories of the past. I don't know what eras this gun has witnessed, but the moment it fires, the past becomes crystal clear."
Weapon_I18N.10304105_Tips:
The custom Judge design is ideal for use by the water. The hovercraft-shaped barrel stabilizes the gun, enhancing its performance.

"I've spent too long thinking; it's time to enter the battlefield. There's still a long journey to my objective."
Weapon_I18N.10304102_Tips:
The custom Judge concept features a cyberpunk theme with a stylish color palette. It's vibrant yet thought-provoking.

"Neon lights haven't yet faded, and dawn remains uncertain. Though the glory of the past remains, under the clashing of steel, the light of civilization no longer shines."
Weapon_I18N.10501104_Tips:
The custom "Beareas" design was hazily sketched by Yvette after a ten-hour sugar crash.

"My hands just... did their thing! Not that I was itching to try the new model or anything."
Weapon_I18N.10501111_Tips:
The special medical edition of Beareas features syringe and tube elements, monitoring opponents' heartbeats in real-time.

“Please... open up to me.”
Weapon_I18N.10501102_Tips:
The custom Beareas model trades its icy look for a corn-themed design symbolizing life and harvest. It's hard not to find it... a bit appetizing.

"Uh... I know you're hungry, but this isn't for making popcorn..."
Weapon_I18N.10501201_Tips:
A special ball edition of Beareas is more compact and lightweight, with added mechanical and gear elements, seamlessly complementing an evening gown.

“I know I'm going to a ball, but I want to bring Fay and my gun... Otherwise, I may feel insecure...”
Weapon_I18N.10501202_Tips:
A special ball edition of Beareas is more compact and lightweight, with added mechanical and gear elements, seamlessly complementing an evening gown.

“I know I'm going to a ball, but I want to bring Fay and my gun... Otherwise, I may feel insecure...”

“I know I'm going to a ball, but I want to bring Fay and my gun... Otherwise, I may feel insecure...”

A special ball edition of Beareas is more compact and lightweight, with added mechanical and gear elements, seamlessly complementing an evening gown.

“I know I'm going to a ball, but I want to bring Fay and my gun... Otherwise, I may feel insecure...”
Weapon_I18N.10301104_Tips:
The Chroma custom model features a cute water gun design. When it fires, the bullets surge like raging waves.

"The sea can be calm, yet it can also swallow everything. Freedom is similar; pursuing it might bring happiness or destruction."
Weapon_I18N.10104113_Tips:
A special underground bar edition of the Shadow Assault, decorated with intricately carved orchids. While most people consider orchids fragile and fragrant, Lawine believes they represent purity and steadfastness.

"If they had a scent, it’d be a cold one."
Weapon_I18N.10104106_Tips:
A custom version of Shadow Assault by Quadrant Foundries, cleverly cloaked in P.U.S. blue and white for stealth.

“By shedding illusions, I've become my true self.”
Weapon_I18N.10104201_Tips:
A personalized Shadow Assault model, featuring plum blossom motifs and classical elements. It embodies legendary heroism and enduring pride, ready to confront any battle alongside its master.

"As snow falls in the dark, the battlefield is wrapped in a frigid embrace. As comrades fell, a lone general stood firm against the gale and snow. The sudden storm buried everything—including, perhaps, the plum tree.
Yet, as a leader, the general remained unyielding, determined to keep her promise beneath the plum blossom.
Surely, once winter passes, the arrival of spring is not far behind."
Weapon_I18N.10104112_Tips:
A camouflage edition of the Shadow Assault, painted by Reiichi to aid stealth in the wilderness. As Lawine and her gun blend in with the earth, ryegrass, wild oats, and countless plants she cannot name sway as she crawls forward.

"Even wild grass has its own charm. Its roots are deep and unyielding."
Weapon_I18N.10112102_Tips:
A special pool party edition of the Gambit. Inspired by seashells, the streamlined design features colors of seawater, beaches, and hibiscus, exuding a retro, romantic feeling.

"Before you play the next song, grab a drink at the bar. The night is still young."
Weapon_I18N.10502103_Tips:
A special underground bar edition of Solo. This is obviously the dance of a peacock.

"Peacock tail feathers? No, these are my eyes watching you."
Weapon_I18N.10303103_Tips:
A custom Dawn model, perfect for waterside use. The barrel sports a trident for an intimidating look.

"A hunter might be watching us at this very moment... Relax. We're the hunters now."
Weapon_I18N.10202106_Tips:
A personalized version of Quasar. Inspired by classic fighter jets, it uses aerodynamics to reduce air resistance when the firearm is in motion—All that's left to figure out now is how to make the gun fly.

“Hmm... Maybe if we stringify the weapon, we can fold it into a paper airplane?”
Weapon_I18N.10202102_Tips:
The tactical custom model of Quasar features an atomic-punk design, offering a more comfortable grip and advanced sights, making it ideal for long-range combat.

"That is the world of atomic-punk.
A world of an unrealistic future, a cold utopia, an eternal realm filled with hidden dangers.
It is a place of hope, fantasy, latent cruelty, and... an inevitably tragic end."
Weapon_I18N.10202104_Tips:
A custom Quasar model featuring many duck-themed elements, symbolizing the courage to ride waves.

“Mission accomplished! Well done, Kokona!”
“Hurry up, we can still make it for the last song!”
Weapon_I18N.10111103_Tips:
A special medical model of Blossom. Features an incense slot and a design that prioritizes usability.

"Can you smell that...? It's the scent of danger."
Weapon_I18N.10111102_Tips:
The Blossom desert edition mimics the process of resin-seeping branches through its material and design. Rumor has it, it releases a woody aroma when fired—though, sadly, the target won't have a chance to enjoy it.

"What a pity. There aren't many flowers in the desert."
Weapon_I18N.10602101_Tips:
A modified version of the Freedom Reign, crafted by Corridor Artisans. It excels in performance, maneuverability, stability, and design concept, making it a groundbreaking achievement of its era.

"In this unfettered era, freedom is more than just a slogan!
So, don't lock me up!"
Weapon_I18N.10602108_Tips:
A special underground bar edition of Freedom Reign. With excessive decorations removed, it is more suitable as an everyday carry.

"Isn't it normal for a bar owner to carry a gun? If danger ever strikes, I need to clear a path to safety for my guests."
Weapon_I18N.10101116_Tips: The Campus Open Day edition of the Inspector features a gamified design to promote the Esports Club. It symbolizes Michele's eagerness to share her passion with others.
Weapon_I18N.10101105_Tips:
This war edition of the Inspector features a built-in pulse system that can influence real battle outcomes.

"A torrent of gunfire reduces everything to ashes. The will for vengeance roars with unyielding fury. We may not know why wars begin, but their means have nothing to do with justice."
Weapon_I18N.10101201_Tips:
The custom Inspector features a white tiger emblem on the dark barrel, glowing with pulsating blue energy. Its wielder, armed with unwavering resolve, charges into the frontlines of justice.

When Michele submitted her modification request, the researchers at Polaris Labs were taken aback, doubting anyone could handle such wild string energy.
“Relax! I’m Michele—harnessing extra string energy is child's play for me!”
Weapon_I18N.10101202_Tips:

When Michele submitted her modification request, the researchers at Polaris Labs were taken aback, doubting anyone could handle such wild string energy.
